 legitimately dispose of them.</p><br><h2><strong>8. Reporting</strong></h2><p>8.1. <i><u>Reporting</u></i>. If the Company or a User has reason to believe that any Content posted on aDoormore violates these Terms and Conditions, intellectual or industrial property law, or any other law, as well as the aDoormore Policy, he/she may report the post by e-mail to: <a href="mailto:support@aDoormore.com">support@aDoormore.com</a>.</p><br><h2><strong>9. Limitations of Services</strong></h2><p>9.1. <i><u>Causes</u></i>. Progetto Doable reserves the right to unilaterally suspend the provision of Services and block access to Users if:</p><ul style="list-style-type: lower-roman"><li>there is reasonable reason to believe that the User’s registration is not authorized by the Company in whose name and on whose behalf it was made;</li><li>there is reasonable reason to believe that Contents shared by Users violates these Terms and Conditions and/or the aDoormore Policy.</li></ul><p>9.2. <i><u>Limitations</u></i>. Limitation of the Services may consist of the deletion of a Content posted by the User up to and including the suspension, temporary or permanent, of the account.</p><br><h2><strong>10. Representations and warranties</strong></h2><p>10.1. The Company represents and warrants:</p><ul style="list-style-type: lower-roman"><li>that it is entitled and has the necessary authorizations to request and use the Services;</li><li>to use the Services only for legitimate purposes;</li><li>that only complete, true and correct information, Contents and personal data are provided by Users;</li><li>to be liable for the system requirements of Users and their access to the Internet;</li><li>to be liable for compliance (and thus Admins, Team Members and Viewers) with the aDoormore Policy;</li><li>to verify that no Content is uploaded that contains viruses, Trojan horses, time bombs, logic bombs and/or other computer programming tools that could even potentially damage, impede or hinder access to aDoormore or the Services or any data or interfere in any way adversely with the Progetto Doable’s business or its infrastructure;</li><li>to supervise and prevent Users from engaging, directly or indirectly, in spamming, phishing, improper, deceptive, or unlawful marketing activities and otherwise harassing Users and related to aDoormore or the Services;</li><li>that it will not download, use, decompile, duplicate or modify aDoormore code;</li><li>that it will not disseminate Contents that could constitute greenwashing activity that could have negative consequences for Progetto Doable; and</li><li>that it will not download to an external medium or otherwise extract Contents published by other Companies on aDoormore.</li></ul><br><h2><strong>11. Subscription</strong></h2><p>11.1. <i><u>Fee</u></i>. Subject to the provisions of Article 14.1.the price of an annual subscription to aDoormore is set at:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Euro 468.00 + VAT if applicable (“<strong>Fee</strong>”).<br>Progetto Doable reserves the right to modify the Fee at any time. Users are entitled to exercise their withdrawal right within 30 days of receiving notice of the modification from Progetto  It is understood that any modification to the Fee made by Progetto Doable will come into effect on the day following the subscription''s expiration date.<br>11.2. <i><u>Payment</u></i>. The Fee for the Services and the Viewer licences, if purchased, shall be paid in advance and shall not be refundable under any circumstances, not even in the event that the Company has not used the Services and the Viewer licences, in whole or in part, during the subscription period, or due to suspension and/or cancellation of the account by Progetto Doable, or due to the User’s choice to cancel the account, technical failures, early termination of the Agreement, etc.<br>11.3. <i><u>Renewal</u></i>. The subscription to aDoormore will be automatically renewed on expiry with automatic charge of the Fee according to the mode chosen during registration or as subsequently indicated by the User. You may cancel the automatic renewal of your subscription at any time before the renewal day, by changing the relevant settings in the User account section.<br>11.4. <i><u>Non-renewal</u></i>. Non-renewal of the subscription shall result in the inability to access the Contents and not in the deletion of the account, which occurs pursuant to Art. 5.8 of these Terms and Conditions.</p><br><h2><strong>12. Liability</strong></h2><p>12.1. <i><u>Limitation</u></i>. Progetto Doable’s liability to the Company, its employees and administrators, is limited in the maximum to the Fee paid by the Company to use the Services during the year in which the damaging event occurred.<br>12.2. <i><u>Exclusions</u></i>. Under no circumstances shall Progetto Doable be liable to the Company, its employees and administrators, for any indirect and consequential damages such as lost revenue, loss of profit, damage to image, loss of chances, caused:</p><ul style="list-style-type: lower-roman"><li>by the malfunctioning of aDoormore, the misuse of Contents and information by the Company and any other hypothetical damage directly attributable to conduct of the Company;</li><li>	malfunctioning of the Services caused by fauilures of telephone lines, power lines, online transmission equipment, overloads, interruptions or any cause beyond the Company’s control;</li><li>from cyber-attacks on the Progetto Doable systems that compromise the integrity or confidentiality of Contents or personal data entered by the Company into aDoormore;</li><li>from the use of aDoormore and the Services by Users or third parties in violation of applicable rules or regulations or in violation of third parties rights; and</li><li>from Contents placed within aDoormore.</li></ul><p>12.3. <i><u>Indemnification</u></i>. The Company agrees to hold harmless and indemnified Progetto Doable, its employees and administrators from any damage, loss, liability, cost, obligation or prejudice they may suffer as a result of the breach of any obligation and/or warranty given under these Terms and Conditions or as a result of any use of aDoormore by the Company and any User associated with it that is unlawful, infringing third party rights or is in breach of the Agreement. The indemnification obligations will survive the duration of the use of aDoormore by the Company and its associated Users until the complete prescription of all rights and possible related actions.</p><br><h2><strong>13. Privacy Policy &amp; Cookie Policy</strong></h2><p>13.1. <i><u>Privacy Policy &amp; Cookie Policy</u></i>. Progetto Doable agrees to process the data provided by the Company and in particular in the execution of this Agreement in accordance with the EU Regulation 2016/679 (the so-called GDPR) for the purposes of its execution. Progetto Doable will retain the personal data shared by the Company in the execution of the Agreement for the duration of the contractual relationship and thereafter for the ordinary ten-year statute of limitations. Progetto Doable will process User’s personal data in compliance with the Privacy Policy available at the following <a href="/privacy" target="_blank">link</a> and the Cookie Policy available at the following <a href="/cookie" target="_blank">link</a> accepted by the Company. User’s use of aDoormore is conditional upon their having read the Privacy Policy and Cookie Policy of aDoormore.</p><br><h2><strong>14. Modification of the Agreement</strong></h2><p>14.1. <i><u>Modifications</u></i>. Progetto Doable reserves the right to amend all or part of the Terms and Conditions set out in the Agreement; in this case, Progetto Doable shall give the User 30 days’ notice before the new Terms and Conditions enter into force: if the User does not request the deletion of his/her account within this period, the new Terms and Conditions shall be deemed accepted.<br>14.2. <i><u>Survival</u></i>. The provisions set forth in the Agreement survive the deactivation and the deletion from the User’s account, whether these have occurred by decision of the User or by initiative of Progetto </p><br><h2><strong>15. Suspension and Modification of aDoormore and/or Services</strong></h2><p>15.1. Progetto Doable will make every reasonable effort to keep aDoormore operational at all times. However, technical issues may cause an interruption in the accessibility and availability of aDoormore. Progetto Doable reserves the right to make changes to aDoormore in order to introduce new features and/or improve the existing Services, their accessibility and/or their operation by giving notice the Companies, possibly also by amending these Terms and Conditions in accordance with the provisions of Article 14 above.</p><br><h2><strong>16. Applicable law and Jurisdiction</strong></h2><p>16.1. <i><u>Italian Law</u></i>. The Terms and Conditions and the Services provided to Users are governed by Italian law to the extent provided by applicable laws and are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Italian Republic.</p><br><h2><strong>17. Jurisdiction</strong></h2><p>17.1. <i><u>Jurisdiction</u></i>. For any dispute arising from the interpretation, application and execution of these Terms and Conditions the Court of Milan shall have jurisdiction.</p><p><br>Pursuant to and for the purposes of Articles 1341 and 1342 of the Italian Civil Code, you acknowledge that you have read and specifically approve the following articles of the Terms and Conditions: Art. 3 “Access to Services”; Art. 4 “aDoormore Policy”; Art. 5 “Account” (par. 5.5, 5.6, 5.7); Art. 6 “Contents”; Art. 7 “User Licence”; Art. 9 "Limitation of Services"; Art. 11 “Subscription”; Art. 12 "Liability"; Art. 14 “Modification of the Agreement”; and Art.17 "Jurisdiction".</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Privacy',N'<h1><strong>aDoormore - Privacy Policy</strong></h1><p>This privacy policy, provided pursuant to Article 13 of the EU Reg. 2016/679 (“<strong>GDPR</strong>”), describes the processing of personal data carried out by Progetto Doable S.r.l. Società Benefit collected through the aDoormore platform (the “<strong>Site</strong>”) and relating to any user who accesses the Site in accordance with the conditions provided for each type of user as defined in the Terms and Conditions of the Site (the “<strong>User</strong>”).</p><h2><strong>1. Controller</strong></h2><p>The Controller is Progetto Doable S.r.l. Società Benefit, with registered office in via Caduti del Lavoro, 13, 25034, Orzinuovi (BS), e-mail: <a href="mailto:privacy@aDoormore.com">privacy@aDoormore.com</a> (“<strong>Progetto Doable</strong>” or the “<strong>Controller</strong>”).</p><h2><strong>2. Categories of data processed</strong></h2><p><i><u>Data communicated by the User</u></i></p><p>The Controller collects personal data that each User enters in the account registration <i>form</i> within the Site such as first name, last name (the so-called personal details), e-mail (the so-called contact data), company role.</p><p><i><u>Data we may automatically collect</u></i></p><p>Cookies are used on the Site to collect and store personal data relating to the use of, access to or interaction through the Site (so-called browsing data) as further described in the <a href="/cookie" target="_blank"><i>Cookie Policy</i></a>.</p><p>(together “<strong>Personal Data</strong>")</p><h2><strong>3. Methods of data processing</strong></h2><p>The Controller processes Users’ Personal Data by taking appropriate security measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, modification or destruction of Personal Data, in accordance with the GDPR.</p><p>Processing is carried out by means of electronic, telematic and/or paper-based tools with organizational methods that are related to the purposes set out below.</p><h2><strong>4. Purpose and legal basis of processing</strong></h2><p>Personal Data collected through the Site will be processed:</p><ul style="list-style-type: none"><li>a) <i>to enable Users to register on the Site.</i> The legal basis for such processing is the performance of the contractual obligations to which the User is a party and/or to take steps at User’s request prior to entering into a contract, and to comply with related legal obligations;</li><li>b) <i>for the management of requests for information forwarded by the User, or for technical assistance.</i> The legal basis for such processing is the performance of the contractual obligations to which the User is a party and/or to take steps at User’s request prior to entering into a contract, and to fulfil related legal obligations;</li><li>c) <i>to enable Users to take advantage of the services offered through the Site.</i> The legal basis is the performance of the contractual obligations at the request of Users and to comply with legal obligations; and</li><li>d) <i>to send e-mail communications regarding other products and services similar and/or complementary to the Site.</i> Pursuant to Article 130 co. 4 of the Privacy Code, such processing has its legal basis in the legitimate interest of the Controller in keeping its Users constantly informed and updated from time to time about the services available on the Site. This legitimate interest is balanced and compatible with the reasonable expectation of the User, since it is reasonable to believe that Users who use a service through the Site are interested in being updated on all the features and services available from time to time on the Site.</li></ul><h2><strong>5. Provision of personal data and consequences if not provided</strong></h2><p>The provision of Personal Data for the purposes set out in points b), c) and d) is optional; refusal to provide Personal Data will make it impossible to access the services offered by the Site, to request technical assistance and to create a personal account.</p><h2><strong>6. Recipients or categories of recipients</strong></h2><p>Personal Data may be made accessible, or disclosed and processed by the following entities, which will be appointed by the Controller, as data processors or persons authorized to process the data, or they will act as autonomous data controllers, according to the case:</p><ul><li>any parent, subsidiary, associated companies of the Controller, employees and/or collaborators in any capacity whatsoever of the Controller and/or any parent, subsidiary, associated companies of the Controller;</li><li>public or private entities, natural or legal persons of which the Controller uses to carry out the activities instrumental to the achievement of the above purpose (<i>e.g.</i> employment consultants) or to which the Controller is obliged to disclose Personal Data, by virtue of legal or contractual obligations; and</li><li>financing or operating partners of the Controller.</li></ul><h2><strong>7. Storage retention period</strong></h2><p>Personal Data may be stored in a form that permits identification of data subjects and for no longer than is necessary for the purposes for which the personal data are processed in accordance with Article 5 of the GDPR; and in particular:</p><ul><li><strong>to provide services through the Site:</strong> Personal Data will be retained for the duration of the contractual relationship, as well as, once it has ended, for the statute of limitations provided for by applicable law;</li><li><strong>for the creation of an Account:</strong> until each User decides to delete his/her account;</li><li><strong>to respond to Users’ requests</strong>: Personal Data will be kept for the period necessary to provide a response to requests for information and/or assistance; and</li><li><strong>to send notices regarding other products and services similar and/or complementary to the Site</strong>: for the duration of the validity of the User’s account to allow him/her to access new services offered and/or available.</li></ul><h2><strong>8. Rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction and data portability</strong></h2><p>Data subjects are granted the rights set out in Articles 15 to 20 of the GDPR.</p><p>By way of example, each interested party may:</p><ul><li>obtain confirmation as to whether or not personal data concerning him are being processed;</li><li>where a processing operation is in progress, obtain access to the personal data concerning him/her and to the information relating to the processing (<i>e.g</i>. the purposes of the processing, the categories of personal data, the recipients or categories of recipients to whom the personal data have been or will be disclosed and, where possible, the storage period) as well as request a copy of the personal data;</li><li>obtain the rectification of inaccurate personal data and the integration of incomplete personal data;</li><li>obtain, if one of the conditions set out in Article 17 of the GDPR applies, the erasure of personal data concerning him/her;</li><li>obtain, in the cases provided for in Article 18 of the GDPR, the restriction of processing;</li><li>request data portability where data are processed automatically on the basis of consent or for the performance of the contract; and</li><li>if the conditions set out in Article 20 of the GDPR are met, receive the personal data concerning him/her in a structured, commonly used and machine-readable format and request their transmission to another data controller, if technically feasible.</li></ul><h2><strong>9. Right to object</strong></h2><p>Each User as a data subject has the right to object at any time to the processing of his/her Personal Data by writing to one of the addresses listed in the Controller Section. In any case, any opposition will not affect the lawfulness of the processing carried out up to that moment.</p><h2><strong>10. Right to lodge a complaint with the Garante</strong></h2><p>Any User as a data subject may lodge a complaint with the <i>Garante per la Protezione dei Dati Personali</i> if he/she considers that his/her rights under the GDPR have been infringed, in accordance with the procedures indicated on the Garante’s website accessible at: <a href="http://www.garanteprivacy.it/" target="_blank">www.garanteprivacy.it</a>.</p><h2><strong>11. Updates</strong></h2><p>This Privacy Policy will be subject to updates. The Controller therefore invites Users who wish to know how personal data collected through the Site are processed to periodically visit this page.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Cookie',N'<h2><strong>aDoormore - Cookie Policy</strong>&nbsp;</h2><p>The specific purpose of this extended policy is to explain the types and methods of using cookies on the <a href="/" target="_blank">aDoormore</a> website (the “<i><strong>Site</strong></i>”), as well as to explain what actions you can take to refuse or delete them.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>1. Controller</strong></h2><p>The Controller is Progetto Doable S.r.l. Società Benefit, with registered office in via Caduti del Lavoro, 13, 25034, Orzinuovi (BS), e-mail:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:privacy@aDoormore.com">privacy@aDoormore.com</a> (“<strong>Progetto Doable</strong>” or the “<strong>Controller</strong>”)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2. Data collected</strong></h2><p>Browsing data and cookies (hereinafter also referred to as "<i><strong>Data</strong></i>”).&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>3. What is a cookie</strong></h2><p>Cookies are small text strings that the sites visited by the user send to the user’s own terminal browser, where they are stored in order to be retransmitted to the same sites the next time the same user visits. In the course of browsing a site, the user may receive “first party” cookies on his terminal, when they are managed directly by the owner and/or operator of the site, and also cookies that are sent from different sites or web servers (“third party” cookies); this happens because on the website visited there may be elements that reside on servers other than the one on which the website is located. In other words, they are those cookies that are set by a website other than the one you are currently visiting.</p><p>Cookies can be distinguished into three different types:</p><ul><li>technical cookies: used for the sole purpose of enabling the site to function properly;</li><li>analytical cookies: used to collect aggregate information of a mainly statistical nature; and</li><li>profiling cookies: aimed at creating profiles relating to the user and used in order to send advertising messages in line with the preferences expressed by the user when browsing the web. <strong>These cookies are not installed by the Site.</strong></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>4. Which cookies are used and for what purpose</strong></h2><p>The cookies implemented on the Site can be technical and analytical. The Site uses the following cookies for the purposes set out below</p><p><i><strong><u>Technical cookies</u></strong></i>&nbsp;</p><p>Technical cookies are used for the sole purpose of carrying out the transmission of a communication over an electronic communications network, or to the extent strictly necessary for the provider of an information society service to provide a service explicitly requested by the user.</p><p>Technical cookies present on the Site can be divided into: navigation or session cookies, which guarantee the normal navigation and use of the Site (for example, allowing to make a purchase or authenticate to access reserved areas). These cookies include functionality cookies, which make it possible to store the choices made by the user on the Site (e.g., language), in order to improve the service rendered to the user.</p><p>The prior consent of the users of the Site is not required for the installation of such cookies.</p><p>The Site uses the following technical cookies:</p><figure style="margin-left: 0px !Important; margin-right: 0px !Important;" class="table table-container"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Cookies</strong>&nbsp;</td><td colspan="3"><strong>Domain</strong>&nbsp;</td><td colspan="2"><strong>Purpose</strong></td><td><strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>scfc</td><td colspan="3">stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Fixes bugs on our site in certain situations by forcing the deletion of the browser cache</td><td>1 year</td></tr><tr><td>stripe.customerportal.csrf</td><td colspan="3">billing.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Preventing attackers from making requests that modify user data in Stripe from other websites</td><td>Session</td></tr><tr><td>locale</td><td colspan="3">.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Check the language on stripe.com to provide a reading experience in the language you expect</td><td>Session</td></tr><tr><td>__stripe_mid</td><td colspan="3">.stripe.com, .billing.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Preventing fraud and assessing the risk associated with a transaction attempt</td><td>1 year</td></tr><tr><td>__stripe_sid</td><td colspan="3">.billing.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Preventing fraud and assessing the risk associated with a transaction attempt</td><td>30 minutes</td></tr><tr><td>cookie-perms</td><td colspan="3">.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Storing users'' cookie authorisations</td><td>6 months</td></tr><tr><td>private_machine_identifier</td><td colspan="3">.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Identify the computer through access sessions and users to prevent fraud.</td><td>1 year</td></tr><tr><td>machine_identifier</td><td colspan="3">.stripe.com</td><td colspan="2">Prevent fraud and allow Stripe to determine the computer used in the Stripe Dashboard.</td><td>1 year</td></tr><tr><td>Asp.Net.Consent</td><td colspan="3">adoormore.com</td><td colspan="2">Cookie Policy from banner</td><td>1 year</td></tr><tr><td>atlassian.xsrf.token</td><td colspan="3">progettoatlassian.net</td><td colspan="2">Preventing XSRF attacks.</td><td>Browser session/closing</td></tr><tr><td>JSESSIONID</td><td colspan="3">progettoatlassian.net</td><td colspan="2">Session tracking</td><td>Browser session/closing</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><strong><u>Analytical cookies</u></strong></i>&nbsp;</p><p>First-party analytical cookies are similar to technical cookies and are used to collect information, in aggregate form, on the number of users and how they visit the Site.</p><p>It should be noted that the Site also uses the following third-party analytical cookies in order to analyze users’ browsing and to produce statistics on visits or to improve the display of content on web pages. These cookies, since the IP address is not in plain text, are assimilated to technical cookies and therefore do not require the user’s consent:</p><figure style="margin-left: 0px !Important; margin-right: 0px !Important;" class="table table-container"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Cookie/Supplier</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Domain</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Purpose</strong></td><td><strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Modalities of elimination</strong></td></tr><tr><td>_ga</td><td><p>.stripe.com,<br>.stripe.events,<br>.go.stripe.global,<br>.stripecdn.com,<br>adoormore.com,</p></td><td>Site analysis and operation</td><td>2 years</td><td>Procedure indicated in point 6</td></tr><tr><td>_gcl_au</td><td>.pay.google.com</td><td>Site Analysis and Advertising</td><td>90 days</td><td>Procedure indicated in point 6</td></tr><tr><td>_gid</td><td>.pay.google.com</td><td>Site analysis and operation</td><td>1 day</td><td>Procedure indicated in point 6</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><i><strong><u>Profiling Cookie</u></strong></i>&nbsp;</p><p>The Site does not use first-party and/or third-party profiling cookies.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>5. Nature of provision of data by users</strong></h2><p>The user of the Site authorizes the use of technical and assimilated cookies by selecting, within the banner containing the brief information, the specific “<i>I understand</i>” button. The provision of Data processed through the installation of technical and analytical cookies, although optional, is necessary to ensure proper navigation within the Site and its proper functioning. If you decide to disable technical and analytical cookies, you will not have access to our services, which cannot be provided without the use of cookies.</p><p>You can change your cookie preferences at any time through specific browser configurations, according to the specific procedures described below. You can also delete cookies installed in the past via your browser preferences.</p><p>As regards third-party cookies, the user may exercise his or her right to object to their processing by informing himself or herself via the third party’s Privacy Policy, via the opt-out link if explicitly provided, or by contacting the third party directly.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>6. Options regarding the use of cookies</strong></h2><p>You can control cookies through the settings of the browser you use. As each browser has slightly different functions, you will have to check the “help” menu of your browser to find out how to change your cookie settings correctly.<br>You can then change your browser settings so that cookies are deleted or not saved on your computer or mobile device without your explicit consent. The user can better understand how to set their browser at the following links:</p><ul><li>Chrome: <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=it" target="_blank">https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=it</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Internet Explorer: <a href="https://windows.microsoft.com/it-IT/internet-explorer/delete-manage-cookies#ie=ie-11" target="_blank">https://windows.microsoft.com/it-IT/internet-explorer/delete-manage-cookies#ie=ie-11</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Opera: <a href="https://help.opera.com/Windows/10.00/it/cookies.html" target="_blank">https://help.opera.com/Windows/10.00/it/cookies.html</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Safari for mobile devices: <a href="https://support.apple.com/kb/HT1677?viewlocale=it_IT" target="_blank">https://support.apple.com/kb/HT1677?viewlocale=it_IT</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Safari for desktop: <a href="https://support.apple.com/kb/PH19214?locale=it_IT" target="_blank">https://support.apple.com/kb/PH19214?locale=it_IT</a>&nbsp;</li><li>Firefox: <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/it/products/firefox/protect-your-privacy/cookies" target="_blank">https://support.mozilla.org/it/products/firefox/protect-your-privacy/cookies</a>&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>7. Data recipients</strong>&nbsp;</h2><p>The Data may be known and processed by the employees of the Controller assigned to the pursuit of the aforementioned purposes, who are expressly authorized to process them and who have received appropriate operating instructions.</p><p>Furthermore, the Data may be communicated to third parties - autonomous data controllers or duly designated as data processors - belonging to the following categories:</p><ol type="A"><li>external parties acting as autonomous data controllers such as, by way of example, authorities and supervisory and control bodies and, in general, to parties, including private parties, entitled to request the data (such as, for example, accounting consultants, legal consultants), Public Authorities that expressly request them for administrative or institutional purposes, in accordance with the provisions of the applicable national and European legislation; and</li><li>third parties who provide services to the Controller and who are useful for the Controller’s activities (e.g. IT service providers for the management of databases, including contact and e-mail databases, digital service providers and IT consultants who provide technical assistance to the Controller, companies that offer support in carrying out market studies); these parties have been specifically appointed as data processors and their names are available upon request to the Controller, using the contact details indicated in Section 9 below.</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>8. Transfer of personal data to countries outside the European Union</strong>&nbsp;</h2><p>Data collected using cookies on the Site will not be transferred outside the European Union.</p><p>Where this is the case, in respect of Data collected using cookies on the Site, the Controller shall, to the extent of its competence, adopt appropriate safeguards, including the applicable adequacy decisions and Standard Contractual Clauses adopted by the European Commission.</p><h2><strong>9. The rights of data subjects</strong>&nbsp;</h2><p>Users, as data subjects (i.e. subjects to whom the Data refer), are holders of the rights conferred by the GDPR. In particular, pursuant to Articles 15-22 of the GDPR, data subjects have the right to request and obtain, at any time, access to their personal data, information on the processing carried out, rectification and/or updating of their personal data, erasure and restriction of processing. They also have the right to object to the processing and to request data portability (i.e. to receive personal data in a structured, machine-readable, commonly used format). Finally, data subjects always have the right to revoke their consent at any time (this, in any case, will not affect the lawfulness of processing carried out on the basis of consent given before revocation) and to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (in Italy the: <i>Garante per la Protezione dei Dati Personali</i>).</p><p>The aforementioned rights may be exercised at any time, by simple request to the Controller to be sent to the contacts indicated in Section 1.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'UnfairTerms',N'<h1><strong>Clausole Vessatorie</strong></h1><p>Art. 3 “Accesso ai Servizi”;<br/>Art. 4 “Regolamento di aDoormore”;<br/>Art. 5 “Account” (par.&nbsp;5.5, 5.6, 5.7);<br/>Art. 6 “Contenuti”;<br/>Art. 7 “Licenza d''''uso”;<br/>Art. 9 “Limitazione dei Servizi”;<br/>Art. 11 “Abbonamento”;<br/>Art. 12 “Responsabilità”;<br/>Art. 14 “Modifica del Contratto”;<br/>Art. 17 “Foro Competente”.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Regulation',N'<h1><strong>aDoormore - aDoormore Policy</strong></h1><p>aDoormore (“<strong>aDoormore</strong>”) is a website and web application owned and managed by Progetto Doable S.r.l. Società Benefit (“<strong>Progetto Doable</strong>”) through which each user (the “<strong>User</strong>”) can share and view information (the “<strong>Contents</strong>”) regarding the field of sustainability, as well as to interact with the Contents shared by other Users (the “<strong>Services</strong>”).</p><p>The purpose of this policy (the “<strong>Policy</strong>”) is to illustrate and regulate the Services provided by aDoormore as well as to provide the usage rules and the standards of conduct that all Users shall observe in relation to Contents.</p><p>Progetto Doable reserves the right to make any changes to the present Policy, notifying the Users accordingly.</p><p>The relationship between the company that subscribes to aDoormore (the “<strong>Company</strong>”) and Progetto Doable is governed by the terms and conditions available at the following <a href="/terms-and-conditions" target="_blank"><i>link</i></a> (the “<strong>Terms and Conditions</strong>”) accepted by the companies that have purchased the subscription (the “<strong>Companies</strong>”).</p><h2><strong>1. Subscription and account types</strong></h2><p>In order to use the Services, aDoormore subscription must be purchased, it is annual and it automatically renews on expiry. The amount is stated in the Terms and Conditions.&nbsp;</p><p>Three types of Users can be linked to each subscription:</p><ul><li>“<strong>Admin</strong>”. Each company has an Admin who can access all Services and who is linked to a unique company e-mail address. The Admin is entitled to:&nbsp;<ul style="list-style-type:none"><li>i) publish Contents in the manner provided by aDoormore;</li><li>ii) put reactions to the Posts (as defined below);</li><li>iii) forward Team Member (as defined below) use codes to their employees;</li><li>iv) acquire access for Viewer (as defined below) accounts;</li><li>v) view the Report (as defined below) contained within the Posts published by other Companies via the Purchase button;</li><li>vi) authorize Team Member accounts to use Admin experience points (XP) to unlock the Report; and</li><li>vii) create customized lists of other Companies to follow according to their own parameters.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li>“<strong>Team Member</strong>” may be assigned by the Admin to a maximum of 20 persons belonging to the Company. The Team Member is entitled to:<ul style="list-style-type:none"><li>i) view Posts within the community;</li><li>ii) put reactions to the Posts; and</li><li>iii) view the Report unlocked by the connected Admin.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li>“<strong>Viewer</strong>” may be assigned by Admin - in the manner described in the section “Invitations” of the Company profile – to individuals internal and/or external to the Company; the number of Viewer accounts that may be purchased is related to the number of Contents published on aDoormore. The Viewer is entitled to:<ul style="list-style-type:none"><li>i) view Posts within the community; and</li><li>ii) view the Reports unlocked by the connected Admin.</li></ul></li></ul><h2><strong>2. Contents</strong></h2><ul><li>aDoormore is a tool for raising awareness and understanding of sustainability issues, as well as for consultation and involvement made available for Companies to enable them to share and monitor the Sustainability Actions (as defined below) undertaken by Companies through the publication of Contents to foster active cooperation between Companies and their supply chain to achieve “sustainable success”.</li><li>aDoormore is a dynamic and proactive ecosystem that aims to promote widespread awareness of ESG (Environmental, Social, Governance) values through the sharing of Contents by Users.</li><li>The Contents are represented by the sustainability actions realized by the Companies and reported to the aDoormore community. By “<strong>Sustainability Actions</strong>” we mean projects, initiatives inspired by ESG values, carried out by Companies to improve the impact of the whole supply chain on the environment, the social community and/or in the interest of their stakeholders (<i>i.e.</i> those who influence and/or are influenced, directly or indirectly, by the activities of a company).</li><li>The “<strong>Post</strong>” is an established format through which Content is shared within the community.</li><li>The “<strong>Report</strong>” is the extensive description of the Sustainability Action undertaken by a Company and included in the Post. It describes the requirements, the Company organization involved, the time taken, the difficulties encountered, and the results achieved in the Sustainability Action carried out.</li></ul><h2><strong>3. Services offered by aDoormore</strong></h2><p>3.1<i> Customized and unique experience for each user</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>Posts, the Weekly top 3, understood as the selection of the Posts that received the most number reactions - <i>"likes"</i> or <i>"to be copied"</i> – in the last 7 days by Admins and/or Team Members. Filters, messaging and profiles followed depend on the preferences indicated, the sectors they belong to and the interests chosen by each User, as set by him/her in his/her <i>account</i>.</p></li></ul><p>3.2<i> Connecting Companies</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>aDoormore allows Companies to connect with each other, helping each user to connect also with groups of Companies on aDoormore they are interested in and share their Contents with them.</p></li></ul><p>3.3<i> Sustainability contents</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>aDoormore allows Companies and Users to express, communicate and share their commitment to sustainability topics. All Contents posted by Users must relate to Sustainability Actions actually undertaken by the Company itself and described through meaningful images and words.</p></li></ul><p>3.4<i> Security and integrity of the site</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>aDoormore promotes the security and integrity of our Services. A team of experts is constantly working to provide Users with a safe and secure experience. In the event that Progetto Doable becomes aware of harmful behavior by Users, it may take appropriate measures to remove it (<i>e.g.</i> User warning, removal of Contents, restriction of functionality, account removal).</p></li></ul><h2><strong>4. User’s commitment to aDoormore and its <i>community</i></strong></h2><p>4.1 <i><strong></strong>Who can use aDoormore</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>The Company in whose name and on whose behalf the registration procedure is completed by an authorized natural person of legal age (<i>i.e.</i>, the Admin); as well as the accounts - Team Member and Viewer - connected to the subscription purchased by the Company.</p></li></ul><p>4.2 <i>Shareable contents at aDoormore</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>Contents must meet the following criteria:</p></li></ul><ul><li>must be actions actually implemented by the Company to which the Admin belongs, relevant to the field of sustainability and consistent with the principles of the UN 2030 Agenda;</li><li>must be communicated in a clear, complete and truthful manner (avoiding “greenwashing” phenomena), as well as in an ethical manner (by way of example, but not limited to, it is not possible to upload images with violent or discriminatory content, etc.);</li><li>Posts shall be related to the sharing of Sustainability Actions carried out by the Company and not to the direct and/or indirect promotion of products or services for commercial purposes of the Company that go beyond what is stated in the Policy; and</li><li>shall not violate any applicable laws and regulations, shall not be unlawful, illegal, defamatory, denigrating, pornographic, obscene or otherwise inappropriate, nor shall they contain incitement to violence, terrorism or hatred in any form.</li></ul><p>4.3 <i>Community Moderation</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>In light of the above criteria, Progetto Doable reserves the right to screen Contents prior to publication on aDoormore and in the event of discrepancies to suspend the publication itself by notifying the Admin who completed the Post publication process. The interpretation of the criteria set out in section 4.2. shall be at the discretion of Progetto Doable, and it is solely aimed at ensuring the consistency of the Contents with the community as described in this Policy. The moderation action carried out by Progetto Doable does not in any way relieve the Companies from full liability in the substance and form of what is published by them, as governed by the Terms and Conditions.</p></li></ul><p>4.4 <i>Editing the Post after publication</i></p><ul style="list-style:none"><li><p>In order to allow Admins to be able to modify Contents into the Post after it has been published, an “<i>Edit</i>” functionality has been introduced.</p><p>Each published version will not overwrite the previous one but will be added to it, and Admins who have unlocked, or will unlock, the Report will be able to view all published versions through the “<i>Timeline</i>” functionality.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>5. Reward mechanism included in the subscription</strong></h2><p>To unlock the Report contained in the Post each Admin must use the experience points (XP) linked to his/her account. To collect the experience points (XP) there is a reward mechanism included in the subscription cost. In particular, 20 experience points (XP) are awarded to the Admin upon initial registration and annual renewal. These experience points (XP) are used to acquire Posts published by other Admins.</p><p>In addition, there is an experience points (XP) reward system linked to Admins’ activity on aDoormore; in particular:</p><ul><li>every time an Admin publishes a Post, he/she receives 10 experience points (XP); and</li><li>each time an Admin purchases a Post, he/she will be charged 1 experience point (XP).</li></ul><p>It is in no way possible to purchase experience points (XP) in addition to those associated with the subscription by paying a financial reward. The internal experience points (XP) rewarding mechanism of aDoormore supports the exchange of Contents between Companies on aDoormore.</p><p>The experience points (XP) status of each Admin will be visible by clicking on the profile icon at the top right of the aDoormore homepage in the “<i>XP points</i>” section.</p><p>Each Admin can authorize his/her Team Members to use experience points (XP) to acquire Posts by changing the settings in the “<i>Invitations</i>” of the Company profile.</p><h2><strong>6. Chat usage</strong></h2><p>The purpose of the aDoormore chat is to facilitate interaction between Admins of Companies regarding published Contents and to encourage discussion between them. Each Admin, should they detect misuse, will be able to block one or more specific Admins, who will no longer be able to communicate with the Admin who blocked them.</p><h2><strong>7. Using Contents in aDoormore</strong></h2><p>The use of Contents in aDoormore is restricted to Admins, while Team Members and Viewers may only view Contents.</p><p>Each User may not <strong>(i)</strong> export, transfer, or copy Contents by any means or in any manner without prior authorization from Progetto Doable; <strong>(ii)</strong> attempt to disable, override, modify, nullify, or otherwise circumvent the Content protection system used within aDoormore; <strong>(iii)</strong> use Contents for commercial or unlawful purposes <strong>(iv)</strong> upload Contents that contain viruses, Trojan horses, time bombs, logic bombs, and/or other computer programming tools that may even potentially damage, prevent, or hinder access to aDoormore or the Services or any data, or interfere in any way negatively with Progetto Doable’s business or its infrastructure <strong>(v)</strong> engage in spamming, phishing, and marketing activities that are improper, deceptive, or unlawful and otherwise likely to harass Users or aDoormore; <strong>(vi)</strong> attempt to download, use, decompile, duplicate, or modify aDoormore code; and <strong>(vii)</strong> disseminate Contents that may constitute greenwashing activity that may adversely affect Progetto </p><h2><strong>8. Account Deletion Request</strong></h2><p>In the event that a Company expressly requests the deletion of its Admin account, as provided in the relevant section within the <a href="/terms-and-conditions" target="_blank">Terms and Conditions</a>, the account will become inaccessible to the Company. It is understood that the Posts already made accessible to other Companies using the Services will remain available to those Companies.</p><h2><strong>9. Exclusion from the <i>community</i></strong></h2><p>In the event of violations of the Terms and Conditions and this Policy, Progetto Doable reserves the right to suspend and/or exclude the Admin and the accounts linked to him/her from the community, giving appropriate notice.</p><p>For frequently asked questions and tips on user experience, please refer to the <a href="/faq" target="_blank"><i>FAQ</i></a>.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Le origini',N'<h2>1. Le origini della sostenibilità</h2> <p>Oggi siamo abituati a pensare al concetto di sostenibilità come legato all’Agenda 2030 dell’ONU, ma è sempre stato così? No, quando si è iniziato a parlare di sostenibilità in tempi recenti lo si è fatto pensando prettamente alla problematica ambientale e legata al consumo delle risorse del pianeta. <br> Facciamo allora un passo indietro e ricapitoliamo gli eventi storici che hanno concorso a definire nel tempo gli eventi storici: </p> <ul> <li>1968: il Club di Roma pubblica il rapporto <i>“The Limits to Growth”</i>. Questa associazione non governativa, non profit formata da scienziati, economisti, capi di Stato di tutti e 5 i continenti, nel suo rapporto attaccava per la prima volta il mito della crescita ed esplorava le interazioni tra i cinque fattori da cui dipende la sorte dell’umanità: <ul> <li>l’aumento della popolazione;</li> <li>la disponibilità di cibo;</li> <li>le riserve e i consumi delle materie prime;</li> <li>lo sviluppo industriale;</li> <li>l’inquinamento.</li> </ul> </li> <li>1972: Conferenza delle Nazioni Unite a Stoccolma. Durante questa conferenza si è posto l’accento sul fatto che per migliorare le condizioni di vita, occorra salvaguardare le risorse naturali a beneficio di tutti e per farlo sarà necessario contare sulla collaborazione internazionale. </li> </ul> <p>Già 50 anni fa si parlava di questi fenomeni, e studiosi e influenti già prevedevano gli impatti disastrosi che il consumismo avrebbe avuto sull’ecosistema. Per 50 anni poco è importato: il progresso e la crescita sono stati sempre più desiderabili rispetto a tematiche più antropologiche come il cambiamento climatico e la vita sulla terra. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Le origini',N'<h2>2. Gli anni più recenti</h2> <ul> <li>1992, durante il <strong>Summit della Terra tenutosi a Rio de Janeiro</strong>, leader mondiali si sono radunati per la prima volta su scala internazionale per discutere le crescenti preoccupazioni ambientali. In quell''occasione, <strong>è stato rafforzato il principio di sviluppo sostenibile</strong>, definito come un modello di crescita capace di soddisfare le esigenze attuali senza precludere alle future generazioni la possibilità di soddisfare le proprie. Questo concetto ha sollevato molteplici problematiche, tra cui la sua natura vaga e indeterminata e l''incapacità di elaborare un approccio pratico e universale applicabile. </li> </ul> <p>Durante la Conferenza sull''ambiente e lo sviluppo del ‘92, è stata creata l''Agenda 21, un piano d''azione che sottolinea l''importanza dell''adesione di tutti i paesi alla risoluzione dei problemi ambientali e sociali. <strong>L''Agenda 21 si basa sull''idea che le società non possono proseguire sul percorso finora seguito senza aggravare le disuguaglianze economiche tra e all''interno delle nazioni</strong>, aumentando povertà, fame, malattie, analfabetismo e danneggiando gli ecosistemi vitali per la nostra sopravvivenza. Questo documento ha aperto la strada a una pianificazione inclusiva su scala mondiale, nazionale e locale. </p> <p>Dieci anni dopo il Summit di Rio, le iniziative dell''Agenda 21 hanno ricevuto <strong>nuovo impulso durante il vertice di Johannesburg</strong> sullo sviluppo sostenibile. L''obiettivo era valutare i progressi ambientali e definire linee guida per promuovere uno stile di vita che rispetti l''ambiente, mirando a unire gli aspetti sociali, economici e ambientali. Tuttavia, si è dovuto ammettere che i risultati ottenuti nel decennio precedente non erano all''altezza delle aspettative. </p>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'Le origini',N'<h2>3. La responsabilità sociale d’impresa</h2> <p>Nel tempo <strong>il concetto di sostenibilità si è evoluto</strong>  passando dal focus sull’ambiente a una visione più ampia che include molti altri elementi. Questo processo evolutivo è avvenuto <strong> a partire dal concetto di responsabilità</strong> che fin dall’inizio era stato parte degli ingredienti della sostenibilità: la <strong>sostenibilità</strong> era stata identificata come una <strong>responsabilità condivisa</strong> a livello globale e vicina, quindi, ad una <strong>responsabilità sociale.</strong> </p> <p>Esistono svariate accezioni del concetto di Responsabilità sociale d’impresa ne citiamo una particolarmente interessante:<br> “Consapevolezza dell’impresa e del suo management delle ricadute sociali che i comportamenti e le decisioni aziendali hanno sulla società civile nel breve come nel medio termine; essa si colloca nella sfera dei comportamenti etici volontari e può essere declinata rispetto ai grandi temi dei diritti umani, dell’ambiente, dello sviluppo sostenibile, della tutela delle minoranze e del Mezzogiorno del mondo, della sicurezza sul lavoro, dello sviluppo professionale dei lavoratori”. <br>L. Hinna, Come gestire la responsabilità sociale d’impresa, Il Sole 24 Ore, Milano 2005. </p> <p>Come si evince, responsabilità sociale d’impresa e sostenibilità si intrecciano. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Le origini',N'<h2>4. L’Agenda 2030</h2> <p>Nel 2015, l’Agenda 21 viene sostituita dall’<strong>Agenda 2030</strong>, un documento sottoscritto dai governi dei 193 Paesi membri delle Nazioni Unite e approvata dall’Assemblea Generale dell’ONU. </p> <p>Possiamo quindi capire il senso dell’Agenda 2030:<br> “<strong>Un piano d’azione per le persone, il pianeta e la prosperità.</strong> È l’Agenda 2030 per lo sviluppo sostenibile sottoscritta il 25 settembre 2015 da 193 paesi delle nazioni Unite, tra cui l’Italia, per condividere l’impegno a garantire un presente e un futuro migliore nel nostro Pianeta e alle persone che lo abitano. </p> <p>L’agenda globale definisce <strong>17 Obiettivi di sviluppo sostenibile da raggiungere entro il 2030</strong>, articolati in <strong>169 target</strong>, che rappresentano una bussola per porre l’Italia e il mondo su un sentiero sostenibile. </p> <p>L’Agenda 2030 porta con sé una grande novità: per la prima volta viene espresso un chiaro <strong>giudizio sull’insostenibilità dell’attuale modello di sviluppo</strong>, non solo sul piano ambientale, ma anche su quello economico e sociale, superando in questo modo definitivamente l’idea che la sostenibilità sia unicamente una questione ambientale e affermando una visione integrata delle diverse dimensioni dello sviluppo”. <br> (Fonte: ASVIS) </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Le origini',N'<h2>5. Conclusioni</h2> <p>È questo il punto di arrivo, per lo meno per quanto ne possiamo sapere oggi, del ragionamento sulla sostenibilità. </p> <p>Come abbiamo visto, a partire dagli anni Settanta il tema ambientale è stato posto all’attenzione dell’opinione pubblica attraverso diverse iniziative internazionali; nel tempo il concetto ha subito un’evoluzione e si è nutrito, possiamo immaginarcelo in questo modo, del concetto di Responsabilità Sociale d’Impresa che, partendo dalla fine dell’Ottocento, a sua volta si stava spostando verso una visione più ampia a tutto tondo. </p> <p>L’Agenda 2030 può essere considerata la sintesi di questo processo e richiama oggi tutti i soggetti a un’attenzione verso una molteplicità di fattori, pensati non come singoli e. alternativi, ma come parti di un sistema: dobbiamo tener conto di tutti questi fattori, nessuno escluso e contemporaneamente. </p> <p>Ovviamente non tutti i soggetti hanno la stessa capacità di incidere su tutti i fattori, ma ognuno deve tenerli a mente tutti, in una logica olistica e di sistema vivente. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'The origins',N'<h2>1. The origins of sustainability</h2> <p>Today, we are used to thinking about the concept of sustainability as linked to the UN''s Agenda 2030, but has it always been so? No, when sustainability began to be discussed in recent times, it was primarily in relation to environmental issues and the consumption of the planet''s resources. <br> Let''s take a step back and recap the historical events that have contributed to defining these issues over time: </p> <ul> <li>1968: The Club of Rome publishes the report <i>"The Limits to Growth."</i> This non-governmental, non-profit association formed by scientists, economists, and heads of state from all five continents attacked the myth of growth for the first time and explored the interactions between the five factors upon which the fate of humanity depends: <ul> <li>Population growth;</li> <li>Availability of food;</li> <li>Reserves and consumption of raw materials;</li> <li>Industrial development;</li> <li>Pollution.</li> </ul> </li> <li>1972: United Nations Conference in Stockholm. During this conference, emphasis was placed on the fact that to improve living conditions, it is necessary to safeguard natural resources for the benefit of all, and to do so, international cooperation will be necessary. </li> </ul> <p>Fifty years ago, these phenomena were already being discussed, and scholars and influencers were already predicting the disastrous impacts that consumerism would have on the ecosystem. For fifty years, little has mattered: progress and growth have been increasingly desirable compared to more anthropological issues such as climate change and life on earth. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'The origins',N'<h2>2. The recent years</h2> <ul> <li>1992, during the <strong> Earth Summit held in Rio de Janeiro</strong>, world leaders gathered for the first time on an international scale to discuss growing environmental concerns. On that occasion, <strong>the principle of sustainable development was strengthened</strong>, defined as a growth model capable of meeting current needs without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs. This concept raised multiple issues, including its vague and indeterminate nature and the inability to develop a practical and universally applicable approach. </li> </ul> <p>During the 1992 Conference on Environment and Development, Agenda 21 was created, an action plan that emphasizes the importance of all countries joining in resolving environmental and social problems. <strong> Agenda 21 is based on the idea that societies cannot continue on the path they have followed so far without exacerbating economic inequalities between and within nations</strong>, increasing poverty, hunger, disease, illiteracy, and damaging ecosystems vital to our survival. This document paved the way for inclusive planning on a global, national, and local scale. </p> <p>Ten years after the Rio Summit, Agenda 21 initiatives received <strong>new momentum during the Johannesburg Summit</strong> on Sustainable Development. The aim was to assess environmental progress and define guidelines for promoting a lifestyle that respects the environment, aiming to integrate social, economic, and environmental aspects. However, it had to be admitted that the results achieved in the previous decade fell short of expectations. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'The origins',N'<h2>3. Corporate social responsibility</h2> <p>Over time, <strong>the concept of sustainability has evolved</strong> rom a focus on the environment to a broader vision that includes many other elements. This evolutionary process has occurred <strong>starting from the concept of responsibility</strong>, which from the beginning had been part of the ingredients of sustainability: sustainability had been identified as a globally <strong>shared responsibility</strong> and, therefore, as a social responsibility. </p> <p>"Corporate awareness and management awareness of the social repercussions that business behaviors and decisions have on civil society in the short and medium term; it falls within the sphere of voluntary ethical behaviors and can be declined concerning the major themes of human rights, the environment, sustainable development, the protection of minorities and the underdeveloped world, workplace safety, and the professional development of workers." <br>L. Hinna, How to manage corporate social responsibility, Il Sole 24 Ore, Milan 2005. </p> <p>As can be seen, corporate social responsibility and sustainability are intertwined. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'The origins',N'<h2>4. Agenda  2030 </h2> <p>In 2015, Agenda 21 was replaced by the <strong>“2030 Agenda”</strong>, a document signed by the governments of the 193 UN member countries and approved by the UN General Assembly. </p> <p>We can then understand the purpose of the 2030 Agenda:<br> “<strong>A plan of action for people, the planet, and prosperity</strong>. It is the 2030 Agenda for sustainable development signed on September 25, 2015, by 193 countries of the United Nations, including Italy, to share the commitment to ensure a better present and future on our planet and to the people who inhabit it. </p> <p>The global agenda defines <strong>17 Sustainable Development Goals to be achieved by 2030</strong>, articulated in <strong>169 targets</strong>, which represent a compass to put Italy and the world on a sustainable path. </p> <p>The 2030 Agenda brings with it a great novelty: for the first time, a clear <strong>judgment is expressed on the unsustainability of the current development model</strong>, not only on the environmental level but also on the economic and social levels, thus definitively overcoming the idea that sustainability is solely an environmental issue and affirming an integrated vision of the different dimensions of development”. <br> (Source: ASVIS) </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'The origins',N'<h2>5. Conclusions</h2> <p>This is the current endpoint, at least as far as we can know today, of the discussion on sustainability. As we have seen, since the 1970s, environmental issues have been brought to the attention of the public through various international initiatives; over time, the concept has evolved and has been nourished, we can imagine it this way, by the concept of Corporate Social Responsibility which, starting from the end of the 19th century, was in turn moving towards a more comprehensive vision. </p> <p>The 2030 Agenda can be considered the synthesis of this process and today calls on all stakeholders to pay attention to a multitude of factors, not conceived as individual and alternative, but as parts of a system: we must take all these factors into account, none excluded and simultaneously. </p> <p>Obviously, not all stakeholders have the same capacity to impact all factors, but everyone must keep them all in mind, in a holistic and living system logic. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Problemi e rischi',N'<h2>1. Qual è il problema?</h2> <p>Potresti pensare che la sostenibilità sia un concetto lontano da te, qualcosa che riguarda altri o che le tue azioni non abbiano un impatto significativo. Forse ritieni che la tua azienda sia troppo piccola per essere coinvolta nella normativa sulla sostenibilità o che i costi di adesione superino i benefici.<br> Ma hai considerato quali potrebbero essere le conseguenze di non adottare un approccio sostenibile? <br> La normativa sulla sostenibilità, infatti, si applica a tutti, in un modo o nell''altro.<br> Al momento, solo le imprese quotate e le grandi aziende sono obbligate a presentare un report di sostenibilità, ma se i tuoi clienti rientrano in queste categorie, anche la tua impresa sarà indirettamente interessata. </p> <p>Ti chiederai come. La legge richiede che l''intera catena del valore sia sostenibile. Ciò significa che non solo le aziende direttamente soggette all''obbligo, ma anche i loro fornitori e stakeholder devono adottare pratiche sostenibili. </p> <p>E quali sono le implicazioni a lungo termine? <br> Le aziende obbligate dalla normativa potrebbero decidere di escludere dalla loro catena del valore quelle imprese che non seguono criteri di sostenibilità, influenzando direttamente la loro sostenibilità complessiva. </p> <p>L''esclusione comporta la perdita di clienti e, conseguentemente, di potenziali entrate a causa della mancata adozione di pratiche sostenibili. Si tratta solamente di una questione di tempo. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Problemi e rischi',N'<h2>2. Quali sono i rischi? </h2> <p>La mancata attuazione di pratiche di sostenibilità da parte di un''azienda può avere un impatto significativo su vari aspetti del suo funzionamento, inclusi quelli economici, finanziari, e le relazioni con clienti e consumatori. <br> Ecco alcuni esempi: <br> <strong>Impatto Economico e Finanziario</strong> </p> <ol> <li><strong>Rischio Reputazionale:</strong> Le aziende che ignorano la sostenibilità possono subire danni alla loro reputazione, il che può tradursi in perdite di clienti e di entrate. </li> <li><strong>Perdita di competitività:</strong> Le aziende non sostenibili possono perdere terreno rispetto ai concorrenti che adottano pratiche sostenibili, diventando meno attraenti per i consumatori consapevoli e per i clienti “BtoB” sottoposti all’obbligo di produrre un report di sostenibilità. </li> <li><strong>Costi operativi elevati:</strong> La mancanza di efficienza energetica e l''uso non ottimale delle materie prime, così come la scarsa attenzione alla valorizzazione delle risorse umane, possono portare a costi operativi più elevati. </li> <li><strong>Rischio di non conformità:</strong> Le aziende possono incorrere in sanzioni legali e finanziarie se non rispettano le normative ambientali sempre più severe. </li> <li><strong>Difficoltà di accesso ai capitali:</strong> Gli investitori e gli istituti di credito stanno sempre più considerando la sostenibilità come un criterio chiave; le aziende non sostenibili possono trovare più difficile accedere al finanziamento. </li> </ol>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'Problemi e rischi',N'<h2>3. Impatto sui clienti e consumatori</h2> <ol> <li><strong> Perdita di fiducia da parte dei consumatori: </strong> I consumatori sono sempre più sensibili alle questioni ambientali e sociali. La mancata adesione a pratiche sostenibili può ridurre la fiducia dei consumatori nell''azienda. </li> <li><strong> Minore coinvolgimento del cliente: </strong> Le aziende non sostenibili possono avere difficoltà a costruire un legame emotivo con i clienti che valutano positivamente l''impegno ambientale. </li> <li><strong> Cambiamento nelle preferenze dei consumatori: </strong> I consumatori possono scegliere di supportare e acquistare i prodotti delle aziende con un forte impegno per la sostenibilità, ignorando quelle che non lo fanno. </li> </ol> <strong> Impatto a Lungo Termine </strong> <ol> <li><strong>Sostenibilità come vantaggio competitivo:</strong> La mancanza di pratiche sostenibili può essere un problema nel lungo termine, man mano che sempre più aziende e settori si muovono verso modelli di business più sostenibili, le aziende che decidono di non aderire saranno progressivamente escluse dal mercato. </li> <li><strong> Adattamento ai cambiamenti del mercato: </strong> Le aziende che non adottano la sostenibilità potrebbero non essere in grado di adattarsi rapidamente ai cambiamenti del mercato che favoriscono prodotti e servizi sostenibili. </li> </ol> <p>La sostenibilità non è più un’opzione “nice to have” ma è diventata essenziale per le strategie aziendali. Ignorarla può danneggiare reputazione, profitto e rapporti con clienti e mercato. Le imprese che adottano pratiche sostenibili si posizionano favorevolmente per le sfide future e le nuove opportunità in un''economia orientata alla sostenibilità. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Problemi e rischi',N'<h2>4. Qual è l''opinione dei clienti nel settore B2B?</h2> <p>I clienti B2B (business-to-business) che sono sottoposti all''obbligo di redigere il bilancio di sostenibilità possono avere varie percezioni e preoccupazioni riguardo ai fornitori che non aderiscono a pratiche ambientali sostenibili: </p> <ol> <li><strong> Allarme per la catena di fornitura: </strong> Le aziende che devono redigere un report di sostenibilità potrebbero vedere i fornitori non sostenibili come un rischio per la loro catena di fornitura. Ciò è dovuto al potenziale impatto negativo sulla loro immagine e responsabilità ambientale, ma anche e soprattutto sull’impatto che può avere sulla sostenibilità del proprio prodotto. </li> <li><strong> Battaglia per la conformità: </strong> Se un''azienda è tenuta a rendicontare aspetti non finanziari, come l''impatto ambientale, avere fornitori non sostenibili potrebbe complicare il proprio impegno nella conformità e nella rendicontazione. </li> <li><strong> Pressione da parte degli stakeholder: </strong> Le aziende con obblighi di rendicontazione non finanziaria spesso affrontano la pressione da parte di stakeholder come investitori, clienti e organizzazioni ambientali. Mantenere relazioni con fornitori non sostenibili può aumentare questa pressione e portare a domande sulla loro serietà nell''affrontare questioni di sostenibilità. </li> <li><strong> Riflessione sui valori aziendali: </strong> Lavorare con fornitori che non adottano pratiche ambientali può essere visto come una contraddizione con i valori aziendali, specialmente se l''azienda si impegna attivamente in pratiche sostenibili. </li> <li><strong> Impatto sulla reputazione: </strong> La collaborazione con fornitori non sostenibili può avere un impatto negativo sulla reputazione dell''azienda, in quanto gli stakeholder potrebbero percepire l''azienda come meno impegnata nella responsabilità ambientale. </li> <li><strong> Difficoltà nella differenziazione sul mercato: </strong> Le aziende che vogliono distinguersi sul mercato per il loro impegno nella sostenibilità potrebbero trovare difficile farlo se la loro catena di fornitura include aziende non sostenibili. </li> <li><strong> Impatto a lungo termine: </strong> A lungo termine, mantenere rapporti con fornitori non sostenibili può essere visto come non strategico, dato che le tendenze di mercato e le normative si stanno spostando sempre più verso la sostenibilità. </li> <li><strong> Costi nascosti del “non sostenibile”: </strong> Ci possono essere costi nascosti associati al lavorare con fornitori non sostenibili, come possibili sanzioni, costi di conformità aggiuntivi e il potenziale per perdite di opportunità di business. </li> </ol> <p>In sintesi, per le aziende B2B che devono redigere il report di sostenibilità, collaborare con fornitori che non aderiscono a pratiche ambientali sostenibili può rappresentare una serie di sfide e rischi. Questo può influenzare la loro decisione in termini di selezione e mantenimento dei fornitori e può portare a una riconsiderazione delle loro partnership commerciali in funzione di una maggiore sostenibilità. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Problemi e rischi',N'<h2>5. Qual è la percezione dei consumatori finali?</h2> <p>Ci sono diversi fattori che influenzano la percezione dei consumatori nei confronti delle aziende che non adottano pratiche di sostenibilità, ad esempio la cultura, l''età, il livello di educazione e la consapevolezza ambientale. Tuttavia, ci sono alcune tendenze generali che possono essere osservate: </p> <ol> <li><strong> Scetticismo e mancanza di fiducia: </strong> I consumatori possono essere scettici riguardo alle aziende che non dimostrano un impegno per la sostenibilità. Questo scetticismo può tradursi in una mancanza di fiducia, una percezione negativa dell''azienda e quindi mancati acquisti. </li> <li><strong> Preferenza per marche responsabili: </strong> Sempre più consumatori preferiscono acquistare da marche che dimostrano responsabilità ambientale e sociale. Le aziende che ignorano la sostenibilità possono perdere questa fascia di mercato. </li> <li><strong> Consapevolezza ambientale: </strong> Con un''educazione e una consapevolezza ambientale in crescita, i consumatori sono più informati e spesso cercano attivamente informazioni sull''impatto ambientale delle aziende da cui acquistano. </li> <li><strong> Influenza sui social media e opinione pubblica: </strong> I social media hanno amplificato la voce dei consumatori, permettendo loro di esprimere disapprovazione contro aziende percepite come non sostenibili. </li> <li><strong>Percezione di valori antiquati:</strong> Le aziende che non adottano misure di sostenibilità possono essere viste come arretrate o non allineate ai valori contemporanei, specialmente dalle generazioni più giovani. </li> <li><strong> Impatto sulle decisioni di acquisto: </strong> La mancanza di sostenibilità può influenzare negativamente le decisioni di acquisto, con i consumatori che scelgono di supportare aziende con pratiche più etiche e sostenibili. </li> <li><strong>Aspettative di responsabilità aziendale:</strong> C''è un''aspettativa crescente che le aziende siano non solo profittevoli, ma anche socialmente e ambientalmente responsabili. </li> <li><strong> Preoccupazione per il futuro: </strong> I consumatori possono essere preoccupati per l''impatto a lungo termine delle pratiche aziendali non sostenibili sull''ambiente e sulla società, portandoli a supportare aziende che considerano seriamente questi problemi. </li> <li><strong>Differenze generazionali:</strong> Le generazioni più giovani, come i Millennials e la Gen Z, tendono a essere più attente alla sostenibilità e possono essere più critici nei confronti delle aziende che non adottano pratiche sostenibili. </li> </ol> <p>I consumatori di oggi sono più informati e consapevoli dell''importanza della sostenibilità. Questa consapevolezza si traduce in aspettative più elevate e una maggiore critica verso le aziende che non mostrano un impegno serio verso pratiche sostenibili. Le aziende che ignorano queste tendenze rischiano di perdere la fiducia e il supporto dei consumatori.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Problems and risks',N'<h2>1. What is the issue?</h2> <p>You might think that sustainability is a concept far removed from you, something that concerns others, or that your actions do not have a significant impact. Perhaps you believe that your company is too small to be involved in sustainability regulations or that the costs of compliance outweigh the benefits.<br> But have you considered what the consequences might be of not adopting a sustainable approach? Sustainability regulations, in fact, apply to everyone, in one way or another.<br> Currently, only listed companies and large corporations are required to produce a sustainability report, but if your clients fall into these categories, your business will also be indirectly affected.<br> </p> <p>You may wonder how. The law requires the entire value chain to be sustainable. This means that not only the companies directly subject to the obligation, but also their suppliers and stakeholders must adopt sustainable practices. </p> <p>And what are the long-term implications?<br> Companies obliged by the regulations may decide to exclude from their value chain those companies that do not follow sustainability criteria, directly affecting their overall sustainability. </p> <p>Exclusion leads to loss of customers and, consequently, potential revenue due to the failure to adopt sustainable practices. It''s only a matter of time. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Problems and risks',N'<h2>2. What are the risks? </h2> <p>The failure to implement sustainability practices by a company can have a significant impact on various aspects of its operations, including economic, financial, and relationships with customers and consumers. <br> Here are some examples: <br> <strong>Economic and Financial Impact</strong> </p> <ol> <li><strong>Reputational Risk:</strong> Companies that ignore sustainability may suffer damage to their reputation, which can result in loss of customers and revenue. </li> <li><strong>Loss of Competitiveness:</strong> Unsustainable companies may lose ground to competitors adopting sustainable practices, becoming less attractive to conscious consumers and "BtoB" customers subject to the obligation to produce a sustainability report. </li> <li><strong>High Operating Costs:</strong> Lack of energy efficiency and suboptimal use of raw materials, as well as poor attention to human resource development, can lead to higher operating costs. </li> <li><strong>Non-Compliance Risk:</strong> Companies may incur legal and financial penalties if they fail to comply with increasingly stringent environmental regulations. </li> <li><strong>Difficulty Accessing Capital:</strong> Investors and credit institutions are increasingly considering sustainability as a key criterion; unsustainable companies may find it more difficult to access financing. </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'Problems and risks',N'<h2>3. Impact on customers and consumers</h2> <ol> <li><strong> Loss of Consumer Trust: </strong> Consumers are increasingly sensitive to environmental and social issues. Failure to adhere to sustainable practices can reduce consumer trust in the company. </li> <li><strong> Reduced Customer Engagement: </strong> Unsustainable companies may struggle to build an emotional bond with customers who value environmental commitment. </li> <li><strong> Shift in Consumer Preferences: </strong> Consumers may choose to support and buy products from companies with a strong commitment to sustainability, ignoring those that do not. </li> </ol> <strong> Long-Term Impact </strong> <ol> <li><strong>Sustainability as a Competitive Advantage:</strong> The lack of sustainable practices can be a problem in the long term, as more and more companies and sectors move towards more sustainable business models, companies that choose not to join will be progressively excluded from the market. </li> <li><strong> Adapting to Market Changes: </strong> Companies that do not adopt sustainability may not be able to adapt quickly to market changes favoring sustainable products and services. </li> </ol> <p>Sustainability is no longer a "nice to have" option but has become essential for business strategies. Ignoring it can damage reputation, profit, and relationships with customers and the market. Companies adopting sustainable practices position themselves favorably for future challenges and new opportunities in a sustainability-oriented economy. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Problems and risks',N'<h2>4. What is the opinion of customers in the B2B sector? </h2> <p>B2B (business-to-business) customers subject to the obligation to produce a sustainability report may have various perceptions and concerns about suppliers that do not adhere to sustainable environmental practices: </p> <ol> <li><strong> Supply Chain Alarm: </strong> Companies required to report sustainability aspects may see unsustainable suppliers as a risk to their supply chain. This is due to the potential negative impact on their environmental image and responsibility but also and above all on the impact it can have on the sustainability of their product. </li> <li><strong> Compliance Battle: </strong> If a company is required to report non-financial aspects, such as environmental impact, having unsustainable suppliers could complicate its commitment to compliance and reporting. </li> <li><strong> Pressure from Stakeholders: </strong> Companies with non-financial reporting obligations often face pressure from stakeholders such as investors, customers, and environmental organizations. Maintaining relationships with unsustainable suppliers can increase this pressure and lead to questions about their seriousness in addressing sustainability issues. </li> <li><strong> Reflection on Corporate Values: </strong> Working with suppliers that do not adopt environmental practices can be seen as a contradiction with corporate values, especially if the company is actively engaged in sustainable practices. </li> <li><strong> Impact on Reputation: </strong> Collaboration with unsustainable suppliers can have a negative impact on the company''s reputation, as stakeholders may perceive the company as less committed to environmental responsibility. </li> <li><strong> Difficulty in Market Differentiation: </strong> Companies that want to stand out in the market for their commitment to sustainability may find it difficult to do so if their supply chain includes unsustainable companies. </li> <li><strong> Long-Term Impact: </strong> In the long term, maintaining relationships with unsustainable suppliers can be seen as unstrategic, given that market trends and regulations are increasingly moving towards sustainability. </li> <li><strong> Hidden Costs of "Non-Sustainable": </strong> There may be hidden costs associated with working with unsustainable suppliers, such as possible penalties, additional compliance costs, and the potential for loss of business opportunities. </li> </ol> <p>In summary, for B2B companies required to report sustainability, collaborating with suppliers that do not adhere to sustainable environmental practices can pose a series of challenges and risks. This can influence their decision in terms of supplier selection and retention and can lead to a reconsideration of their business partnerships in terms of greater sustainability. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Problems and risks',N'<h2>5. What is the perception of final consumers?</h2> <p>There are several factors influencing consumer perception of companies that do not adopt sustainability practices, such as culture, age, level of education, and environmental awareness. However, there are some general trends that can be observed: </p> <ol> <li><strong> Skepticism and Lack of Trust: </strong> Consumers may be skeptical of companies that do not demonstrate a commitment to sustainability. This skepticism can translate into a lack of trust, a negative perception of the company, and therefore lost purchases. </li> <li><strong> Preference for Responsible Brands: </strong> More and more consumers prefer to buy from brands that demonstrate environmental and social responsibility. Companies that ignore sustainability may lose this market segment. </li> <li><strong> Environmental Awareness: </strong> With growing education and environmental awareness, consumers are more informed and often actively seek information on the environmental impact of the companies they buy from. </li> <li><strong>Influence on Social Media and Public Opinion:</strong> Social media have amplified the voice of consumers, allowing them to express disapproval against companies perceived as unsustainable. </li> <li><strong> Perception of Outdated Values: </strong> Companies that do not adopt sustainability measures may be seen as outdated or not aligned with contemporary values, especially by younger generations. </li> <li><strong>Impact on Purchasing Decisions:</strong> The lack of sustainability can negatively influence purchasing decisions, with consumers choosing to support companies with more ethical and sustainable practices. </li> <li><strong> Expectations of Corporate Responsibility: </strong> There is a growing expectation that companies are not only profitable but also socially and environmentally responsible. </li> <li><strong>Concern for the Future:</strong> Consumers may be concerned about the long-term impact of unsustainable business practices on the environment and society, leading them to support companies that take these issues seriously. </li> <li><strong>Generational Differences:</strong> Younger generations, such as Millennials and Gen Z, tend to be more attentive to sustainability and may be more critical of companies that do not adopt sustainable practices. </li> </ol> <p>Today''s consumers are more informed and aware of the importance of sustainability. This awareness translates into higher expectations and greater criticism towards companies that do not show a serious commitment to sustainable practices. Companies that ignore these trends risk losing the trust and support of consumers.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>1. Quadro di riferimento internazionale per il concetto di sostenibilità</h2> <p><strong>Rispetto a quale quadro di riferimento internazionale si snoda il concetto di sostenibilità?</strong> <br> L’ Agenda 2030 e la sua visione olistica che ricopre 17 ambiti. <br> <br> <strong>Come si traduce concretamente l’agenda 2030 nel ruolo richiesto alle aziende?</strong> <br> Si traduce concretamente in 6 ambiti di azione </p> <ul> <li>Ambiente </li> <li>Sostenibili verso i clienti </li> <li>Cooperazione con aziende e comunità </li> <li>Benessere dei dipendenti </li> <li>Organizzazione trasparenza </li> <li>Filiera sostenibile </li> </ul> <p>Questi ambiti di azione li trovi nelle “categorie di aDoormore” dove potrai trovare le sottocategorie che le compongono e le azioni e le pratiche richieste alle aziende. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>2. A quali aziende è richiesto fare questo percorso di sostenibilità?</h2> <p>Il percorso di sostenibilità si rivolge a tutte le aziende indistintamente. Tra queste aziende la normativa europea CSRD identifica alcune tipologie di aziende che sono obbligate:</p> <ul> <li>Enti di interesse Pubblico rilevanti;</li> <li>Grandi aziende non quotate;</li> <li>PMI quotate, istituzioni creditizie piccole e non complesse, imprese assicurative “captive”.</li> </ul> <p><strong>Se la mia azienda non ha le caratteristiche che riconducono all’obbligo normativo, posso farne a meno?</strong><br> Anche se la tua azienda non presenta le caratteristiche che impongono il rispetto di specifici obblighi normativi, non è possibile esimersi completamente da tali responsabilità. Questo è particolarmente vero se l''azienda opera come fornitore per un''altra impresa soggetta a obblighi normativi. Le aziende soggette a questi obblighi sono tenute a implementare pratiche sostenibili non solo nelle proprie operazioni interne, ma anche lungo l''intera catena di fornitura, come specificato nella sezione “categorie di sostenibilità” alla voce "filiera sostenibile" di aDoormore. Pertanto, è necessario che queste aziende monitorino e si assicurino che i loro fornitori adottino e seguano un piano d''azione coerente con queste pratiche sostenibili. </p>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>3. Che cosa sono chiamate a fare le aziende assoggettate alla norma con la propria filiera?</h2> <p>Le aziende soggette a specifiche normative sono tenute a garantire che la loro catena di fornitura sia sostenibile. Questo obbligo implica la necessità di mappare e monitorare che i fornitori adottino comportamenti responsabili e predispongano un piano d''azione adeguato in materia di sostenibilità. Ciò significa che, al di là dei criteri tradizionali quali il costo, i tempi di consegna, la qualità del prodotto, le condizioni di garanzia, e i servizi aggiuntivi, che in passato costituivano i fattori determinanti, ora la sostenibilità diviene il criterio prioritario. Se questa condizione preliminare non è soddisfatta, la relazione commerciale rischia seriamente di essere compromessa, dato che le aziende al vertice della catena di fornitura non possono permettersi di collaborare con fornitori non sostenibili. È importante notare che, nella valutazione dei fornitori (vendor rating), la sostenibilità assume un''importanza crescente, influenzando significativamente la decisione finale. Per le imprese che attirano l''attenzione pubblica, l''importanza della sostenibilità si amplifica ulteriormente, raggiungendo un impatto tale che l''assenza di pratiche sostenibili può portare a penalizzazioni nelle relazioni di compravendita talmente gravi da non essere bilanciabili attraverso nessuna forma di incentivo o condizione commerciale vantaggiosa. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>4. Come fanno le aziende assoggettate alla norma a capire il posizionamento sostenibile di un fornitore?</h2> <p>Queste imprese utilizzano ciò che viene definito come "rating di sostenibilità" per valutare le loro pratiche ambientali, sociali ed economiche. Sul mercato operano diverse entità accreditate capaci di emettere questi rating, riconosciuti e valorizzati a livello commerciale. Per ottenere un rating, le aziende devono essere oggetto di una valutazione basata su questionari specifici che indagano l''implementazione delle pratiche di sostenibilità all''interno delle loro operazioni. Questo processo richiede anche la presentazione di documentazione supportiva che confermi l''accuratezza delle informazioni fornite. Al completamento della valutazione, l''ente emittente il rating fornisce una scheda di valutazione che certifica il livello di sostenibilità dell''azienda. Tipicamente, i punteggi si articolano in tre o quattro categorie: se si ottengono valutazioni più elevate esse migliorano l''attrattiva dell''azienda sul mercato, accrescendo la sua competitività. Qualora un''azienda riceva una valutazione inferiore alla soglia minima, le viene richiesto di elaborare un piano di miglioramento, seguito da una successiva rivalutazione. Di conseguenza, non è ammesso avere un punteggio al di sotto di un certo livello, ed è mandatorio raggiungere e superare tale soglia. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>5. C’è qualcuno che mi aiuta ad avere contenuti ed esperienze per rispondere ai rating?</h2><p>Purtroppo, l''approccio più diffuso tra le aziende capo-filiera consiste nel demandare ai fornitori il compito e l''obbligo di soddisfare determinati standard minimi e di adottare misure adeguate a raggiungere tali obiettivi. A volte, queste aziende offrono corsi di formazione volti a fornire una comprensione basilare del tema, ma questi non cambiano il principio secondo cui ogni fornitore deve adeguarsi e migliorarsi autonomamente. Se stai leggendo questo, significa che la tua azienda è in una posizione privilegiata, poiché uno dei tuoi principali clienti ha scelto di supportarti attivamente nel tuo percorso verso la sostenibilità. Questo dimostra che tiene a te e desidera vederti crescere e migliorare: insieme, la vostra collaborazione è più solida.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>6. Come posso massimizzare questa opportunità?</h2> <p>L’azienda capo filiera che ti ha invitato utilizza aDoormore per monitorare il tuo percorso nella logica di supportarti. Per poterlo fare ti chiede di dare evidenza di tutte quelle pratiche di sostenibilità adottate nella propria azienda.  Tutto ciò che non vedrà in aDoormore è qualcosa che dovrà assumere non sia stato realizzato. L''obiettivo di questa iniziativa non è semplicemente valutare e classificare i fornitori per escluderli o includerli, ma piuttosto monitorare e assistere il loro sviluppo, aiutandoli a prepararsi adeguatamente per rispondere ai criteri di valutazione o per migliorare gli aspetti che sono stati giudicati deboli o insufficienti. Questo processo offre un vantaggio doppio: </p> <ul> <li>garantisce la visibilità necessaria ai requisiti del capo filiera e, contemporaneamente, contribuisce alla comunità fornendo pratiche di valore che altri possono considerare di adottare e replicare. </li> <li>si crea una rete di supporto affidabile, ricordando che la sostenibilità si basa su collaborazione e interdipendenza. </li> </ul> <p>Come sottolineiamo nella nostra login page a questo punto la sostenibilità conviene: moltiplichiamo le azioni individuali per condividerne i risultati. Tutti più resilienti, competitivi e con un impatto positivo per società e ambiente. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>7. Ci sono aree che l’azienda capo-filiera considera maggiormente prioritarie di altre?</h2> <p>Sì, ogni anno l''azienda capo filiera identifica specifiche categorie e aree di interesse su cui concentrarsi nel lavoro con i propri fornitori. Queste categorie, considerate particolarmente significative e prioritarie, rientrano nella strategia di sviluppo sostenibile dell''azienda e sono denominate "materiali" ovvero ambiti maggiormente rilevanti e prioritari. Puoi trovare un dettaglio di queste categorie nella sezione "white paper" accessibile dal menù in alto a destra nell’homepage. La scelta di questi ambiti indica un''attenzione particolare dell''azienda capo filiera verso di essi; tuttavia, ciò non esclude l''importanza di altri ambiti, ma evidenzia una maggiore sensibilità verso quelli selezionati. È importante sottolineare che la sostenibilità abbraccia un''ampia gamma di aspetti e che, per essere fornitori sostenibili, è necessario adoperarsi in maniera trasversale in tutte le categorie. Inoltre, oltre ad adempiere alle richieste del proprio capo filiera, è cruciale anche che ogni fornitore individui e definisca le proprie priorità (materialità) per sviluppare efficacemente il proprio percorso di sostenibilità. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funziona',N'<h2>8. Se volessi offrire la stessa opportunità di cui sto beneficiando anche alla mia filiera, ne avrei la possibilità?</h2> <p>Assolutamente si. Significherebbe diventare Ambassador di Progetto Doable e concedere a sé stessi ed alla propria filiera di beneficiare di tutti i vantaggi garantiti dalla logica di collaborazione in contrasto con la logica di competizione a cui sarebbero fisiologicamente destinate. Per maggiori informazioni visitare il sito internet www.progettodoable.it. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>1. International reference framework for the concept of sustainability</h2> <p><strong>What international framework does the concept of sustainability align with?</strong> <br> The concept of sustainability aligns with the Agenda 2030 and its holistic vision covering 17 areas. <br> <br> <strong>How does the Agenda 2030 translate into the role required of companies?</strong> <br> It translates into 6 concrete areas of action: </p> <ul> <li>Environment </li> <li>Sustainable towards customers </li> <li>Cooperation with companies and communities </li> <li>Employee well-being </li> <li>Organizational transparency </li> <li>Sustainable supply chain </li> </ul> <p>You can find these areas of action in the “aDoormore categories” where you can find the subcategories that compose them and the actions and practices required of companies. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>2. Which companies are required to take this sustainability path?</h2> <p>The sustainability pathway is aimed at all companies without distinction. Among these companies, the European CSRD regulation identifies certain types of companies that are obligated:</p> <ul> <li>Relevant Public Interest Entities;</li> <li>Large non-listed companies;</li> <li>Listed SMEs, small and non-complex credit institutions, and "captive" insurance undertakings.</li> </ul> <p><strong>If my company does not have the characteristics that lead to regulatory obligations, can I do without it?</strong><br> Even if your company does not have the characteristics that require compliance with specific regulatory obligations, it is not possible to completely exempt oneself from such responsibilities. This is particularly true if the company operates as a supplier to another company subject to regulatory obligations. Companies subject to these obligations are required to implement sustainable practices not only in their own internal operations but also throughout the entire supply chain, as specified in the "sustainability categories" section under the "sustainable supply chain" of aDoormore. Therefore, it is necessary for these companies to monitor and ensure that their suppliers adopt and follow an action plan consistent with these sustainable practices. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>3. What are companies subject to the regulation expected to do with their supply chain?</h2> <p>Companies subject to specific regulations are required to ensure that their supply chain is sustainable. This obligation implies the need to map and monitor that suppliers adopt responsible behaviors and develop an adequate action plan on sustainability. This means that, beyond traditional criteria such as cost, delivery times, product quality, warranty conditions, and additional services, which in the past constituted the determining factors, now sustainability becomes the priority criterion. If this preliminary condition is not met, the business relationship risks being seriously compromised, as top-tier companies in the supply chain cannot afford to collaborate with non-sustainable suppliers. It is important to note that, in supplier evaluation (vendor rating), sustainability assumes increasing importance, significantly influencing the final decision. For companies that attract public attention, the importance of sustainability is further amplified, reaching an impact such that the absence of sustainable practices can lead to penalties in trading relationships so severe that they cannot be balanced through any form of incentive or advantageous commercial condition. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>4. How do companies subject to the regulation understand a supplier''s sustainable positioning?</h2> <p>These companies use what is termed as "sustainability rating" to assess their environmental, social, and economic practices. Several accredited entities operate in the market capable of issuing these ratings, recognized and valued at the commercial level. To obtain a rating, companies must undergo an evaluation based on specific questionnaires that investigate the implementation of sustainability practices within their operations. This process also requires the submission of supporting documentation confirming the accuracy of the information provided. Upon completion of the evaluation, the rating issuer provides an assessment card certifying the company''s level of sustainability. Typically, scores are divided into three or four categories: if higher ratings are achieved, they enhance the company''s attractiveness in the market, increasing its competitiveness. If a company receives a rating below the minimum threshold, it is required to develop an improvement plan, followed by a subsequent reassessment. Consequently, having a score below a certain level is not allowed, and it is mandatory to reach and exceed that threshold. </p>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>5. Is there anyone who helps me get content and experiences to meet ratings?</h2> <p>Unfortunately, the most widespread approach among lead companies is to delegate to suppliers the task and obligation to meet certain minimum standards and to adopt measures to achieve these objectives. Sometimes, these companies offer training courses aimed at providing a basic understanding of the topic, but these do not change the principle that each supplier must adjust and improve autonomously. If you are reading this, it means that your company is in a privileged position since one of your main customers has chosen to actively support you on your sustainability journey. This demonstrates that they care about you and want to see you grow and improve: together, your collaboration is stronger. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>6. How can I maximize this opportunity?</h2> <p>The lead company in the supply chain that has invited you uses aDoormore to monitor your progress with the aim of supporting you. In order to do this, they ask you to provide evidence of all the sustainability practices adopted in your own company. Anything they do not see in aDoormore is something they will assume has not been implemented. The goal of this initiative is not simply to assess and classify suppliers to exclude or include them, but rather to monitor and assist in their development, helping them adequately prepare to meet evaluation criteria or to improve aspects that have been judged weak or insufficient. This process offers a dual advantage: </p> <ul> <li>It ensures the visibility necessary for the requirements of the lead company and, at the same time, contributes to the community by providing valuable practices that others may consider adopting and replicating. </li> <li>It creates a reliable support network, remembering that sustainability is based on collaboration and interdependence. </li> </ul> <p>As we emphasize on our login page, sustainability pays off at this point: we multiply individual actions to share their results. Everyone becomes more resilient, competitive, and has a positive impact on society and the environment. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>7. Are there areas that the lead company considers more of a priority than others?</h2> <p>Yes, every year the lead company identifies specific categories and areas of interest to focus on in its work with its suppliers. These categories, considered particularly significant and prioritized, fall within the company''s sustainable development strategy and are called "material" areas, meaning they are the most relevant and prioritized areas. You can find details of these categories in the "white paper" section accessible in the menu at the top right of the homepage. The choice of these areas indicates a particular attention of the lead company towards them; however, this does not exclude the importance of other areas, but highlights a greater sensitivity towards those selected. It is important to emphasize that sustainability embraces a wide range of aspects and that, to be sustainable suppliers, it is necessary to work transversally in all categories. Furthermore, in addition to fulfilling the requests of their lead company, it is crucial for each supplier to identify and define their own priorities (materiality) to effectively develop their sustainability path. </p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How it works',N'<h2>8. If I wanted to offer the same opportunity that I am benefiting from to my supply chain, would I be able to?</h2> <p>Absolutely yes. It would mean becoming an Ambassador of Progetto Doable and granting oneself and one''s supply chain all the advantages guaranteed by the logic of collaboration, as opposed to the logic of competition to which they would be physiologically destined. For more information, visit www.progettodoable.it. </p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come posso creare un account Admin?',N'Clicca sul pulsante “Abbonati” presente nella pagina di accesso.<ol><li>Inserisci il codice invito. </li><li>Compila i campi obbligatori e clicca su “Registrati”. </li><li>Seleziona il piano di abbonamento annuale e procedi con il pagamento. </li></ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I create an Admin account?',N'<p>Click on the "Subscribe" button on the login page.</p><ol> <li> <p>Enter the invitation code.</p> </li> <li> <p>Fill in the required fields and click &quot;Sign up&quot;.</p> </li> <li> <p>Select the annual subscription plan and proceed with the payment.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come posso acquistare le licenze Viewer?',N'<p><strong>Come posso acquistare le licenze Viewer?</strong></p> <p>Le licenze Viewer possono essere acquistate dall&rsquo;utente Admin e maturano quanti pi&ugrave; <em>post</em> vengono pubblicati. Attualmente sono disponibili 4 tipologie di pacchetti di licenze Viewer, che puoi visualizzare nella sezione &quot;Inviti e pacchetti&quot; nel Profilo azienda oppure nel menu principale in home page.</p> <p>Puoi acquistare fino ad un massimo di 10 pacchetti per ogni tipologia.</p> <p>Una volta sbloccato l&rsquo;ultimo pacchetto potrai acquistare i pacchetti senza limiti di quantit&agrave;.</p> <br> <p>Per acquistare un pacchetto di licenze:</p> <ol> <li>All&rsquo;interno del Profilo azienda o del menu in home page clicca su&nbsp;&ldquo;Inviti e pacchetti&rdquo;.</li> <li>Entra nella sezione &ldquo;Pacchetti&rdquo;</li> <li>Seleziona la quantit&agrave; di pacchetti sbloccati che risponde alle tue esigenze e procedi all&rsquo;acquisto scegliendo la modalit&agrave; di pagamento tra bonifico bancario e carta di credito.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <ul> <li>Nel caso del pagamento con bonifico bancario riceverai le istruzioni per procedere con il bonifico e il pacchetto dovr&agrave; essere rinnovato manualmente di anno in anno.</li> <li>Nel caso del pagamento con carta di credito verrai rimandato su Stripe per completare il pagamento.</li> <li>Inoltre, ogni pacchetto ha durata di un anno e si rinnova in automatico.</li> </ul> <p>Per cambiare metodo di pagamento o annullare il pacchetto hai tempo fino al giorno antecedente alla scadenza del pacchetto.</p> <br> <p>Per annullare un pacchetto di licenze:</p> <br> <br> <ol> <li>Clicca su&nbsp;&ldquo;Account e piano&rdquo;&nbsp;all&rsquo;interno del Profilo azienda o del menu in home page.</li> <li>Entra nella sezione &ldquo;Abbonamento&rdquo;.</li> <li>Ora clicca su &ldquo;Gestisci abbonamento&rdquo;, qui ti verr&agrave; mostrato un riepilogo dei piani attivi. In ogni momento potrai gestire i dati di pagamento di ciascun piano oppure decidere di annullare l&rsquo;abbonamento.</li> </ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I purchase Viewer licenses?',N'<p>Viewer licenses can be purchased by the Admin user and are earned as more <em>posts</em> are published. Currently, there are 4 types of Viewer license packages available, which can be viewed in the "Invites and packages" section under your Company profile or in the main menu on the homepage.
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'Come posso gestire gli utenti?',N'<p>L&rsquo;utente Admin pu&ograve; gestire gli utenti invitati all&rsquo;interno del Profilo azienda cliccando su&nbsp;&ldquo;Inviti e pacchetti&rdquo;.<br>All&rsquo;interno della maschera inviti pu&ograve; fare le seguenti azioni:</p> <ol> <li> <p>Attribuire agli utenti Team Member i permessi per sbloccare i post;</p> </li> <li> <p>Assegnare agli utenti Viewer un pacchetto di licenze con scadenza diversa rispetto a quello iniziale;</p> </li> <li> <p>Revocare l&rsquo;invito a uno o pi&ugrave; utenti Team Member;</p> </li> <li> <p>Revocare l&rsquo;invito a uno o pi&ugrave; utenti Viewer.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I manage users?',N'<p>The Admin user can manage the users invited to the Company Profile by clicking on &quot;Invitations and packages.&quot;<br>Within the invitations section, the Admin can perform the following actions:</p><ol> <li> <p>Grant Team Member users the permissions to unlock&nbsp;<em>posts</em>;</p> </li> <li> <p>Assign Viewer users a license package with a different expiration date than the initial one;</p> </li> <li> <p>Revoke the invitation to one or more Team Member users;</p> </li> <li> <p>Revoke the invitation to one or more Viewer users.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come posso creare un post?',N'<p>Il&nbsp;post&nbsp;pu&ograve; essere creato solo dall&rsquo;utente Admin, che rappresenta l&rsquo;azienda in aDoormore.</p> <ol> <li> <p>Clicca su &ldquo;Crea un nuovo post&rdquo; presente nella tua homepage o nel Profilo azienda.</p> </li> <li> <p>Compila tutti i campi presenti.</p> </li> <li> <p>Infine, clicca su &ldquo;Conferma ed invia a redazione&rdquo; per la pubblicazione.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I create a post?',N'<p>A&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;can only be created by the Admin user, who represents the company on aDoormore.</p><ol> <li> <p>Click on &quot;Create a new post&quot; on your homepage or in the Company profile.</p> </li> <li> <p>Fill in all the required fields.</p> </li> <li> <p>Finally, click on &quot;Confirm and submit&quot; for publication.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come posso modificare un post già pubblicato?',N'<p>Nella sezione Profilo azienda:</p> <ol> <li> <p>Clicca sulla sezione &ldquo;Post pubblicati&rdquo;</p> </li> <li> <p>Clicca sul&nbsp;post&nbsp;che desideri modificare.</p> </li> <li> <p>Clicca su &ldquo;Modifica&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p>Applica le modifiche desiderate (ad esempio: aggiunta di una nuova lingua,piccole correzioni di forma o aggiornamento dei risultati).</p> </li> <li> <p>Ora clicca su:</p> <ul> <li> <p>&ldquo;Salva bozza&rdquo;, se desideri rivederlo in un secondo momento prima di pubblicarlo.</p> </li> <li> <p>&ldquo;Conferma ed invia a redazione&rdquo; per inviare il&nbsp;post&nbsp;alla redazione per la pubblicazione.</p> </li> </ul> </li> </ol> <p>Una volta pubblicato, troverai accanto al titolo del post la funzionalit&agrave; &ldquo;Cronologia&rdquo;. Qui potrai vedere tutte le versioni del post che sono state pubblicate nel tempo.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I edit a published post?',N'<p>In the Company profile section:</p><ol> <li> <p>Click on the &quot;Published posts&quot; section.</p> </li> <li> <p>Click on the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;you want to edit.</p> </li> <li> <p>Click on &quot;Edit.&quot;</p> </li> <li> <p>Apply the desired changes (e.g., adding a new language, small formatting corrections, or updating the results).</p> </li> <li> <p>Now click on:</p> <ul> <li> <p>&quot;Save as draft&quot; if you want to review it later before publishing.</p> </li> <li> <p>&quot;Confirm and submit&quot; to send the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;to the editorial team for publication.</p> </li> </ul> </li> </ol><p>Once published, you will find the &quot;History&quot; feature next to the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;title. Here, you can view all the versions of the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;that have been published over time.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'In che formato possono essere caricate le immagini?',N'<p>Le immagini possono essere caricate nei formati ammessi (JPEG, PNG).</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'In what formats can images be uploaded?',N'<p>Images can be uploaded in the supported formats (JPEG, PNG).</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Nel campo immagine, posso caricare un documento che non è presente tra i formati indicati?',N'<p>No, non &egrave; possibile. Ad esempio, se vuoi mostrare uno schema organizzativo che hai in formato Word, PowerPoint, PDF o altro, puoi facilmente fare uno screenshot e caricarlo.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'In the image field, can I upload a document that is not listed among the indicated formats?',N'<p>No, it is not possible. For example, if you want to display an organizational chart that you have in Word, PowerPoint, PDF, or another format, you can easily take a screenshot and upload it.</p>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'È possibile salvare una bozza del post che sto creando?',N'<p>S&igrave;, puoi sospendere la creazione del post in qualsiasi momento e riprendere quando preferisci. Nella maschera di creazione del post, clicca su &ldquo;Salva bozza&rdquo; in alto a destra. Per riprendere vai nella sezione &ldquo;Bozze&rdquo; all&rsquo;interno del Profilo azienda e clicca sul post che vuoi continuare a modificare</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Is it possible to save a draft of the post I am creating?',N'<p>Yes, you can suspend the creation of the post at any time and resume it whenever you like. In the post creation interface, click on “Save as draft” in the upper right corner. To resume, go to the “Drafts” section within the Company profile and click on the post you want to continue editing.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'È possibile creare bozze di più post contemporaneamente?',N'<p>Si, se inizi a scrivere un post puoi salvarlo come bozza e contemporaneamente puoi salvare come bozza anche altri post che hai iniziato a creare. Per visualizzare tutti post salvati come bozza e riprendere con la creazione vai nella sezione “Bozze” all’interno del Profilo azienda e clicca sul post che vuoi continuare a modificare.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Is it possible to create drafts of multiple posts simultaneously?',N'<p>Yes, if you start writing a post, you can save it as a draft, and at the same time, you can also save other posts you have started creating as drafts. To view all posts saved as drafts and continue creating, go to the “Drafts” section within the Company profile and click on the post you want to continue editing.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'È possibile pubblicare i post in più lingue?',N'<p>Si, &egrave; possibile pubblicare il post in pi&ugrave; lingue.</p> <p>Nella maschera di creazione del&nbsp;<em>post</em>:</p> <ol> <li> <p>Clicca su &ldquo;Aggiungi lingua&rdquo; per selezionare le lingue in cui vuoi scrivere il&nbsp;<em>post</em>.</p> </li> <li> <p>Scegli poi quale di queste &egrave; la tua lingua principale, quella con cui vuoi presentarti alla&nbsp;<em>community</em>&nbsp;cliccando sul flag &ldquo;Imposta come lingua predefinita&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p>Assicurati di inserire la traduzione di tutti i campi del post per ogni lingua aggiunta.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'en',N'Is it possible to publish posts in multiple languages?',N'<p>Yes, it is possible to publish the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;in multiple languages.<br>In the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;creation interface:</p><ol> <li> <p>Click on &ldquo;Add language&rdquo; to select the languages in which you want to write the&nbsp;<em>post</em>.</p> </li> <li> <p>Then choose which of these is your primary language, the one you want to present to the community by clicking on the flag &ldquo;Set as default language&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p>Make sure to enter the translation of all&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;fields for each added language.</p> </li> </ol>'),
	 (N'it',N'È possibile cercare un’azienda?',N'<p>Si, è possibile. Per ricercare un’azienda utilizza lo strumento di ricerca presente nella barra di navigazione in alto nella tua homepage.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Is it possible to search for a company?',N'<p>Yes, it is possible. To search for a company, use the search tool located in the navigation bar at the top of your homepage.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'È possibile seguire un’azienda?',N'<p>Si, è possibile. All’interno del profilo dell’azienda selezionata clicca su “Segui profilo” per seguire le sue azioni di sostenibilità.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'Is it possible to follow a company?',N'<p>Yes, it is possible. Within the profile of the selected company, click on “Follow profile” to keep up with its sustainability actions.</p>');
INSERT INTO "Document" ("CultureInfo","Title","Body") VALUES
	 (N'it',N'Come posso creare un raggruppamento di aziende seguite?',N'<p>Nel menu principale della tua home page:</p> <ol> <li> <p>Clicca su&nbsp;&ldquo;Seguiti&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p>Ora ti comparir&agrave; una maschera per gestire i segmenti.</p> </li> <li> <p>Clicca su &ldquo;Gestisci i segmenti&rdquo;. Qui potrai modificare i segmenti esistenti o crearne di nuovi cliccando su &ldquo;Aggiungi un segmento&rdquo;.</p> </li> </ol> <p>Una volta creati i segmenti potrai attribuirli alle aziende che segui direttamente dal profilo dell&rsquo;azienda seguita cliccando nell&rsquo;apposito spazio dedicato ai segmenti presente nella sezione di destra &nbsp;della pagina.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How can I create a group of followed companies?',N'<p>In the main menu of your homepage:</p><ol> <li> <p>Click on &ldquo;Followed&rdquo;</p> </li> <li> <p>A management interface for segments will appear.</p> </li> <li> <p>Click on &ldquo;Manage segments&rdquo; Here you can modify existing segments or create new ones by clicking on &ldquo;Add a segment&rdquo;<br><br></p> </li> </ol> <p>Once the segments are created, you can assign them to the companies you follow directly from the profile of the followed company by clicking in the dedicated segment area on the right side of the page.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funzionano i filtri di ricerca?',N'<p>Nella colonna di sinistra della tua homepage &egrave; presente la sezione &ldquo;Filtra post&rdquo;. Qui sar&agrave; possibile visualizzare i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;in base ai criteri desiderati.</p> <ul> <li> <p>Barra di ricerca: puoi cercare uno specifico&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;digitando il nome del&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;o dell&rsquo;azienda che lo ha creato.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Periodo</em>: puoi selezionare un arco temporale predefinito (Giorno, Settimana, Mese o Anno) in cui visualizzare i&nbsp;<em>post</em>. Oppure inserire una data personalizzata.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Categorie Sostenibilit&agrave;</em>: puoi scegliere di visualizzare i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;negli ambiti di sostenibilit&agrave; di tuo interesse. Ad esempio: &ldquo;Ambiente&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Categorie Azienda</em>: puoi selezionare i settori di appartenenza delle aziende che hanno pubblicato i&nbsp;<em>post</em>. Ad esempio: &ldquo;Aeronautica&rdquo;.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Dimensione Azienda</em>: puoi selezionare la dimensione delle aziende che hanno pubblicato i&nbsp;<em>post</em>.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Nazioni</em>: puoi scegliere le nazioni a cui appartengono le aziende di cui vuoi conoscere le iniziative.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Aziende seguite</em>: puoi visualizzare i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;delle aziende seguite.</p> </li> </ul> <p>&Egrave; inoltre possibile selezionare pi&ugrave; filtri contemporaneamente per visualizzare diverse combinazioni di&nbsp;<em>post</em>.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How do the search filters work?',N'<p>In the left column of your homepage, there is a section called &ldquo;Filter Posts.&rdquo; Here, you can view&nbsp;<em>posts</em>&nbsp;based on your desired criteria.</p><ul> <li> <p><em>Search Bar</em>: You can search for a specific&nbsp;<em>post&nbsp;</em>by typing the name of the&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;or the company that created it.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Period</em>: You can select a predefined time frame (Day, Week, Month, or Year) to view the&nbsp;<em>posts</em>. Alternatively, you can enter a custom date.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Sustainability Categories</em>: You can choose to view&nbsp;<em>posts</em>&nbsp;in the sustainability areas of your interest. For example: &ldquo;Environment.&rdquo;</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Company Categories</em>: You can select the sectors to which the companies that published the&nbsp;<em>posts</em>&nbsp;belong.&nbsp;<em>For example: &ldquo;Aerospace.&rdquo;</em></p> </li> <li> <p><em>Company</em>&nbsp;Size: You can select the size of the companies that published the&nbsp;<em>posts</em>.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Countries</em>: You can choose the countries to which the companies whose initiatives you want to know about belong.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Followed Companies</em>: You can view posts from the companies you follow.</p> </li> </ul>'),
	 (N'it',N'È possibile interagire con i post?',N'<p>Ogni&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;prevede delle interazioni.</p> <p>Clicca sulle rispettive icone sotto il&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;per interagire.</p> <ul> <li> <p><em>Mi piace</em>:&nbsp;permette di condividere il tuo apprezzamento rispetto all&rsquo;iniziativa condivisa. Disponibile anche per l&rsquo;utente Team Member.<em>Azione da copiare</em>:&nbsp;permette di condividere la tua intenzione a replicare l&rsquo;iniziativa condivisa. Disponibile anche per l&rsquo;utente Team Member.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Sblocca</em>: permette all&rsquo;Admin di sbloccare l&rsquo;intero contenuto del&nbsp;<em>post</em>. &nbsp;e all&rsquo;utente Team Member di inviare una notifica all&rsquo;utente Admin per invitarlo a valutare lo sblocco del&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;selezionato.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Preferiti</em>: permette di salvare il&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;nella lista dei preferiti. Disponibile anche per l&rsquo;utente Team Member.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Leggi</em>: permette di visualizzare l&rsquo;iniziativa nel dettaglio ed &egrave; disponibile per i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;gi&agrave; sbloccati. Disponibile anche per l&rsquo;utente Team Member e Viewer.</p> </li> </ul>'),
	 (N'en',N'Can I interact with the posts?',N'<p>Each post supports various interactions. Click on the respective icons below the post to interact.</p><ul> <li> <p><em><span>Like</span></em><strong><span>:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;allows you to share your appreciation for the shared initiative. Also available for Team Member users.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Action to copy</span></em><strong><span>:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;allows you to express your intention to copy the shared initiative. Also available for Team Member users.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Unlock</span></em><strong><span>:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;allows the Admin to unlock the entire content of the&nbsp;</span><em><span>post</span></em><span>&nbsp;and enables Team Member users to send a notification to the Admin inviting them to consider unlocking the selected&nbsp;</span><em><span>post</span></em><span>.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Favorites</span></em><strong><span>:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;allows you to save the&nbsp;</span><em><span>post</span></em><span>&nbsp;in your favorites list. Also available for Team Member users.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Read</span></em><strong><span>:</span></strong><span>&nbsp;allows you to view the initiative in detail and is available for already unlocked&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>. Also available for Team Member and Viewer users.</span></p> </li> </ul>'),
	 (N'it',N'Come funzionano i "preferiti"?',N'<p>&Egrave; possibile aggiungere i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;alla lista dei preferiti. Questa informazione &egrave; visibile solo all&apos;utente Admin e agli utenti Team Member dell&apos;azienda. Per visualizzare i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;preferiti clicca su &ldquo;Preferiti&rdquo; disponibile nella sezione Profilo azienda.</p>'),
	 (N'en',N'How do "Favorites" work?',N'<p>You can add&nbsp;<em>posts</em>&nbsp;to your favorites list. This information is only visible to the Admin user and the Team Members of the company. To view your favorite&nbsp;<em>posts</em>, click on &quot;Favorites&quot; available in the Company profile section.</p>'),
	 (N'it',N'Quali informazioni sono disponibili nella sezione Profilo azienda?',N'<p>Nella sezione Profilo azienda troverai:</p> <ul> <li> <p><em>Post pubblicati</em>: tutti i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;che hai pubblicato.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Post sbloccati</em>: tutti i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;pubblicati da altre aziende che hai sbloccato per conoscerne i dettagli.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Preferiti</em>: tutti i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;che hai contrassegnato come preferiti.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Azioni da copiare</em>: tutte le azioni che ti piacerebbe replicare.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Bozze</em>: tutti i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;che hai iniziato a creare e che hai salvato come bozza. Questa sezione &egrave; disponibile solo per gli utenti Admin.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Respinti</em>: tutti i&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;revisionati dalla Redazione e respinti, con i relativi suggerimenti ai fini dell&rsquo;approvazione. Questa sezione &egrave; disponibile solo per gli utenti Admin.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Account e piano</em>: tutte le informazioni relative alla tua azienda che verranno visualizzate dagli altri utenti della&nbsp;<em>community, la sezione per aggiornare la password e per la gestione dell&rsquo;abbonamento</em>.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Inviti e pacchetti</em>: la sezione per gestire tutti gli inviti a Team Member e Viewer e per acquistare nuovi pacchetti Viewer.</p> </li> <li> <p><em>Analytics</em>: tutte le statistiche inerenti alle attivit&agrave; che hai fatto in aDoormore e ai&nbsp;<em>post</em>&nbsp;che hai pubblicato.</p> </li> </ul>'),
	 (N'en',N'What information is available in the Company profile section?',N'<p>In the Company profile section, you will find:</p><ul> <li> <p><em><span>Published posts</span></em><span>: all the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;you have published.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Unlocked</span></em><span>&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>: all the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;published by other companies that you have unlocked to view their details.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Favorites</span></em><span>: all the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;you have marked as favorites.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><span>Actions to copy: all the actions you would like to replicate.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Drafts</span></em><span>: all the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;you have started creating and saved as drafts. This section is only available to Admin users.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Rejected</span></em><span>: all the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;reviewed by the Editorial Team and rejected, along with their suggestions for approval. This section is only available to Admin users.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Account and plan</span></em><span>: all the information related to your company that will be visible to other users in the community, the section to update your password, and manage your subscription.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Invitations and packages</span></em><span>: the section to manage all invitations to Team Members and Viewers and to purchase new Viewer packages.</span></p> </li> <li> <p><em><span>Analytics</span></em><span>: all the statistics related to your activities on aDoormore and the&nbsp;</span><em><span>posts</span></em><span>&nbsp;you have published.</span></p> </li> </ul>');
